347private final static void buildFile(String filename, List listToDump) {
348        BufferedWriter writer = null;
349        try {
350                writer = new BufferedWriter(new FileWriter(filename));
351            for (Iterator iterator = listToDump.iterator(); iterator.hasNext(); ) {
352                    writer.write(String.valueOf(iterator.next()));
353            }
354            writer.flush();
355        } catch(IOException e) {
356                // ignore
357        } finally {
358                if (writer != null) {
359                try {
360                                writer.close();
361                        } catch (IOException e1) {
362                                // ignore
363                        }
364                }
365        }
366        System.out.println(filename + " creation complete"); //$NON-NLS-1$
367}
368private final static String[] buildFileForName(String filename, String contents) {
369        String[] result = new String[contents.length()];
370        result[0] = null;
371        int resultCount = 1;
372 
373        StringBuffer buffer = new StringBuffer();
374 
375        int start = contents.indexOf("name[]"); //$NON-NLS-1$
376        start = contents.indexOf('\"', start);
377        int end = contents.indexOf("};", start); //$NON-NLS-1$
378 
379        contents = contents.substring(start, end);
380 
381        boolean addLineSeparator = false;
382        int tokenStart = -1;
383        StringBuffer currentToken = new StringBuffer();
384        for (int i = 0; i < contents.length(); i++) {
385                char c = contents.charAt(i);
386                if(c == '\"') {
387                        if(tokenStart == -1) {
388                                tokenStart = i + 1;
389                        } else {
390                                if(addLineSeparator) {
391                                        buffer.append('\n');
392                                        result[resultCount++] = currentToken.toString();
393                                        currentToken = new StringBuffer();
394                                }
395                                String token = contents.substring(tokenStart, i);
396                                if(token.equals(ERROR_TOKEN)){
397                                        token = INVALID_CHARACTER;
398                                } else if(token.equals(EOF_TOKEN)) {
399                                        token = UNEXPECTED_EOF;
400                                }
401                                buffer.append(token);
402                                currentToken.append(token);
403                                addLineSeparator = true;
404                                tokenStart = -1;
405                        }
406                }
407                if(tokenStart == -1 && c == '+'){
408                        addLineSeparator = false;
409                }
410        }
411        if(currentToken.length() > 0) {
412                result[resultCount++] = currentToken.toString();
413        }
414 
415        buildFileForTable(filename, buffer.toString().toCharArray());
416 
417        System.arraycopy(result, 0, result = new String[resultCount], 0, resultCount);
418        return result;
419}
420private static void buildFileForReadableName(
421        String file,
422        char[] newLhs,
423        char[] newNonTerminalIndex,
424        String[] newName,
425        String[] tokens) {
426 
427        ArrayList entries = new ArrayList();
428 
429        boolean[] alreadyAdded = new boolean[newName.length];
430 
431        for (int i = 0; i < tokens.length; i = i + 3) {
432                if("1".equals(tokens[i])) { //$NON-NLS-1$
433                        int index = newNonTerminalIndex[newLhs[Integer.parseInt(tokens[i + 1])]];
434                        StringBuffer buffer = new StringBuffer();
435                        if(!alreadyAdded[index]) {
436                                alreadyAdded[index] = true;
437                                buffer.append(newName[index]);
438                                buffer.append('=');
439                                buffer.append(tokens[i+2].trim());
440                                buffer.append('\n');
441                                entries.add(String.valueOf(buffer));
442                        }
443                }
444        }
445        int i = 1;
446        while(!INVALID_CHARACTER.equals(newName[i])) i++;
447        i++;
448        for (; i < alreadyAdded.length; i++) {
449                if(!alreadyAdded[i]) {
450                        System.out.println(newName[i] + " has no readable name"); //$NON-NLS-1$
451                }
452        }
453        Collections.sort(entries);
454        buildFile(file, entries);
455}
456private static void buildFilesForRecoveryTemplates(
457        String indexFilename,
458        String templatesFilename,
459        char[] newTerminalIndex,
460        char[] newNonTerminalIndex,
461        String[] newName,
462        char[] newLhs,
463        String[] tokens) {
464 
465        int[] newReverse = computeReverseTable(newTerminalIndex, newNonTerminalIndex, newName);
466 
467        char[] newRecoveyTemplatesIndex = new char[newNonTerminalIndex.length];
468        char[] newRecoveyTemplates = new char[newNonTerminalIndex.length];
469        int newRecoveyTemplatesPtr = 0;
470 
471        for (int i = 0; i < tokens.length; i = i + 3) {
472                if("3".equals(tokens[i])) { //$NON-NLS-1$
473                        int length = newRecoveyTemplates.length;
474                        if(length == newRecoveyTemplatesPtr + 1) {
475                                System.arraycopy(newRecoveyTemplates, 0, newRecoveyTemplates = new char[length * 2], 0, length);
476                        }
477                        newRecoveyTemplates[newRecoveyTemplatesPtr++] = 0;
478 
479                        int index = newLhs[Integer.parseInt(tokens[i + 1])];
480 
481                        newRecoveyTemplatesIndex[index] = (char)newRecoveyTemplatesPtr;
482 
483                        String token = tokens[i + 2].trim();
484                        java.util.StringTokenizer st = new java.util.StringTokenizer(new String(token), " ");  //$NON-NLS-1$
485                        String[] terminalNames = new String[st.countTokens()];
486                        int t = 0;
487                        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
488                                terminalNames[t++] = st.nextToken();
489                        }
490 
491                        for (int j = 0; j < terminalNames.length; j++) {
492                                int symbol = getSymbol(terminalNames[j], newName, newReverse);
493                                if(symbol > -1) {
494                                        length = newRecoveyTemplates.length;
495                                        if(length == newRecoveyTemplatesPtr + 1) {
496                                                System.arraycopy(newRecoveyTemplates, 0, newRecoveyTemplates = new char[length * 2], 0, length);
497                                        }
498                                        newRecoveyTemplates[newRecoveyTemplatesPtr++] = (char)symbol;
499                                }
500                        }
501                }
502        }
503        newRecoveyTemplates[newRecoveyTemplatesPtr++] = 0;
504        System.arraycopy(newRecoveyTemplates, 0, newRecoveyTemplates = new char[newRecoveyTemplatesPtr], 0, newRecoveyTemplatesPtr);
505 
506        buildFileForTable(indexFilename, newRecoveyTemplatesIndex);
507        buildFileForTable(templatesFilename, newRecoveyTemplates);
508}
509private static void buildFilesForStatementsRecoveryFilter(

512                char[] newLhs,
513                String[] tokens) {
514 
515                char[] newStatementsRecoveryFilter = new char[newNonTerminalIndex.length];
516 
517                for (int i = 0; i < tokens.length; i = i + 3) {
518                        if("4".equals(tokens[i])) { //$NON-NLS-1$
519                                int index = newLhs[Integer.parseInt(tokens[i + 1])];
520 
521                                newStatementsRecoveryFilter[index] = 1;
522                        }
523                }
524                buildFileForTable(filename, newStatementsRecoveryFilter);
525        }

527private static void buildFilesForFlags(

544private static void buildFileForCompliance(
545                String file,
546                int length,
547                String[] tokens) {
548 
549                byte[] result = new byte[length * 8];
550 
551                for (int i = 0; i < tokens.length; i = i + 3) {
552                        if("2".equals(tokens[i])) { //$NON-NLS-1$
553                                int index = Integer.parseInt(tokens[i + 1]);
554                                String token = tokens[i + 2].trim();
555                                long compliance = 0;
556                                if("1.4".equals(token)) { //$NON-NLS-1$
557                                        compliance = ClassFileConstants.JDK1_4;
558                                } else if("1.5".equals(token)) { //$NON-NLS-1$
559                                        compliance = ClassFileConstants.JDK1_5;
560                                } else if("recovery".equals(token)) { //$NON-NLS-1$
561                                        compliance = ClassFileConstants.JDK_DEFERRED;
562                                }
563 
564                                int j = index * 8;
565                                result[j] =         (byte)(compliance >>> 56);
566                                result[j + 1] = (byte)(compliance >>> 48);
567                                result[j + 2] = (byte)(compliance >>> 40);
568                                result[j + 3] = (byte)(compliance >>> 32);
569                                result[j + 4] = (byte)(compliance >>> 24);
570                                result[j + 5] = (byte)(compliance >>> 16);
571                                result[j + 6] = (byte)(compliance >>> 8);
572                                result[j + 7] = (byte)(compliance);
573                        }
574                }
575 
576                buildFileForTable(file, result);
577        }
578private final static void buildFileForTable(String filename, byte[] bytes) {

583                } catch(IOException e) {
584                // ignore
585        } finally {
586                        if (stream != null) {
587                                try {
588                                        stream.close();
589                                } catch (IOException e1) {
590                                        // ignore
591                                }
592                        }
593                }

595        }
596        private final static void buildFileForTable(String filename, char[] chars) {
597                byte[] bytes = new byte[chars.length * 2];
598                for (int i = 0; i < chars.length; i++) {
599                        bytes[2 * i] = (byte) (chars[i] >>> 8);
600                        bytes[2 * i + 1] = (byte) (chars[i] & 0xFF);
601                }
602 
603         java.io.FileOutputStream stream = null;
604                try {
605                        stream = new java.io.FileOutputStream(filename);
606                        stream.write(bytes);
607                } catch(IOException e) {
608                // ignore
609        } finally {
610                        if (stream != null) {
611                                try {
612                                        stream.close();
613                                } catch (IOException e1) {
614                                        // ignore
615                                }
616                        }
617                }
618                System.out.println(filename + " creation complete"); //$NON-NLS-1$
619        }
620        private final static byte[] buildFileOfByteFor(String filename, String tag, String[] tokens) {
621 
622                //transform the String tokens into chars before dumping then into file
623 
624                int i = 0;
625                //read upto the tag
626                while (!tokens[i++].equals(tag)){/*empty*/}
627                //read upto the }
628 
629                byte[] bytes = new byte[tokens.length]; //can't be bigger
630                int ic = 0;
631                String token;
632                while (!(token = tokens[i++]).equals("}")) { //$NON-NLS-1$
633                        int c = Integer.parseInt(token);
634                        bytes[ic++] = (byte) c;
635                }
636 
637                //resize
638                System.arraycopy(bytes, 0, bytes = new byte[ic], 0, ic);
639 
640                buildFileForTable(filename, bytes);
641                return bytes;
642        }

688public final static void buildFilesFromLPG(String dataFilename, String dataFilename2)        {
689 
690        //RUN THIS METHOD TO GENERATE PARSER*.RSC FILES
691 
692        //build from the lpg javadcl.java files that represents the parser tables
693        //lhs check_table asb asr symbol_index
694 
695        //[org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.internal.compiler.parser.Parser.buildFilesFromLPG("d:/leapfrog/grammar/javadcl.java")]
696        char[] contents = CharOperation.NO_CHAR;
697        try {
698                contents = Util.getFileCharContent(new File(dataFilename), null);
699        } catch (IOException ex) {
700                System.out.println(Messages.parser_incorrectPath);
701                return;
702        }
703        java.util.StringTokenizer st =
704                new java.util.StringTokenizer(new String(contents), " \t\n\r[]={,;");  //$NON-NLS-1$
705        String[] tokens = new String[st.countTokens()];
706        int j = 0;
707        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
708                tokens[j++] = st.nextToken();
709        }
710        final String prefix = FILEPREFIX;
711        int i = 0;
712 
713        char[] newLhs = buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "lhs", tokens); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$
714        buildFileOfShortFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "check_table", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
715        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "asb", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
716        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "asr", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
717        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "nasb", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
718        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "nasr", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
719        char[] newTerminalIndex = buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "terminal_index", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
720        char[] newNonTerminalIndex = buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "non_terminal_index", tokens); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$
721        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "term_action", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
722 
723        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_prefix", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
724        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_suffix", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
725        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_lhs", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
726        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_state_set", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
727        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_rhs", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
728        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_state", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
729        buildFileOfIntFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "in_symb", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
730 
731        byte[] newRhs = buildFileOfByteFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "rhs", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
732        buildFileOfByteFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "term_check", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
733        buildFileOfByteFor(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", "scope_la", tokens); //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-1$
734 
735        String[] newName = buildFileForName(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", new String(contents)); //$NON-NLS-1$
736 
737        contents = CharOperation.NO_CHAR;
738        try {
739                contents = Util.getFileCharContent(new File(dataFilename2), null);
740        } catch (IOException ex) {
741                System.out.println(Messages.parser_incorrectPath);
742                return;
743        }
744        st = new java.util.StringTokenizer(new String(contents), "\t\n\r#");  //$NON-NLS-1$
745        tokens = new String[st.countTokens()];
746        j = 0;
747        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
748                tokens[j++] = st.nextToken();
749        }
750 
751        buildFileForCompliance(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", newRhs.length, tokens);//$NON-NLS-1$
752        buildFileForReadableName(READABLE_NAMES_FILE+".properties", newLhs, newNonTerminalIndex, newName, tokens);//$NON-NLS-1$
753 
754        buildFilesForRecoveryTemplates(
755                        prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", //$NON-NLS-1$
756                        prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", //$NON-NLS-1$
757                        newTerminalIndex,
758                        newNonTerminalIndex,
759                        newName,
760                        newLhs,
761                        tokens);
762 
763        buildFilesForStatementsRecoveryFilter(
764                        prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", //$NON-NLS-1$
765                        newNonTerminalIndex,
766                        newLhs,
767                        tokens);
768 
769        buildFilesForFlags(
770                        prefix + (++i) + ".rsc", //$NON-NLS-1$
771                        rhs.length,
772                        tokens);
773 
774 
775        System.out.println(Messages.parser_moveFiles);
776}
777public static int in_symbol(int state) {

780public final static void initTables() throws java.io.IOException {
781 
782        final String prefix = FILEPREFIX;
783        int i = 0;
784        lhs = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
785        char[] chars = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
786        check_table = new short[chars.length];
787        for (int c = chars.length; c-- > 0;) {
788                check_table[c] = (short) (chars[c] - 32768);
789        }
790        asb = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
791        asr = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
792        nasb = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
793        nasr = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
794        terminal_index = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
795        non_terminal_index = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
796        term_action = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
797 
798        scope_prefix = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
799        scope_suffix = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
800        scope_lhs = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
801        scope_state_set = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
802        scope_rhs = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
803        scope_state = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
804        in_symb = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
805 
806        rhs = readByteTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
807        term_check = readByteTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
808        scope_la = readByteTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
809 
810        name = readNameTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
811 
812        rules_compliance = readLongTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
813 
814        readableName = readReadableNameTable(READABLE_NAMES_FILE_NAME);
815 
816        reverse_index = computeReverseTable(terminal_index, non_terminal_index, name);
817 
818        recovery_templates_index = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
819        recovery_templates = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
820 
821        statements_recovery_filter = readTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
822        state_flags = readByteTable(prefix + (++i) + ".rsc"); //$NON-NLS-1$
823 
824        base_action = lhs;
825 
826    optionalSemicolonState =new boolean[base_action.length];
827        for ( i = 0; i < optionalSemicolonState.length; i++) {
828                if (base_action[i]+TokenNameSEMICOLON<term_check.length
829                                && (term_check[base_action[i]+TokenNameSEMICOLON] == TokenNameSEMICOLON))
830                {
831                        int act=term_action[base_action[i]+TokenNameSEMICOLON];
832                        if (act>ERROR_ACTION)
833                                act-=ERROR_ACTION;
834                        boolean isEmptyStatementsState = false;
835                        if (act<NUM_RULES)
836                                isEmptyStatementsState = (state_flags[act]&FLAG_EMPTY_STATEMENT)>0;
837                        if (!isEmptyStatementsState)
838                                optionalSemicolonState[i]=true;
839                }
840        }
841

849protected static int original_state(int state) {
850        return -base_check(state);
851}
852protected static int[] computeReverseTable(char[] newTerminalIndex, char[] newNonTerminalIndex, String[] newName) {
853        int[] newReverseTable = new int[newName.length];
854        for (int j = 0; j < newName.length; j++) {
855                found : {
856                        for (int k = 0; k < newTerminalIndex.length; k++) {
857                                if(newTerminalIndex[k] == j) {
858                                        newReverseTable[j] = k;
859                                        break found;
860                                }
861                        }
862                        for (int k = 0; k < newNonTerminalIndex.length; k++) {
863                                if(newNonTerminalIndex[k] == j) {
864                                        newReverseTable[j] = -k;
865                                        break found;
866                                }
867                        }
868                }
869        }
870        return newReverseTable;
871}
872 
873private static int getSymbol(String terminalName, String[] newName, int[] newReverse) {
874        for (int j = 0; j < newName.length; j++) {
875                if(terminalName.equals(newName[j])) {
876                        return newReverse[j];
877                }
878        }
879        return -1;
880}

882protected static byte[] readByteTable(String filename) throws java.io.IOException {
883 
884        //files are located at Parser.class directory
885 
886        InputStream stream = Parser.class.getResourceAsStream(filename);
887        if (stream == null) {
888                throw new java.io.IOException(Messages.bind(Messages.parser_missingFile, filename));
889        }
890        byte[] bytes = null;
891        try {
892                stream = new BufferedInputStream(stream);
893                bytes = Util.getInputStreamAsByteArray(stream, -1);
894        } finally {
895                try {
896                        stream.close();
897                } catch (IOException e) {
898                        // ignore
899                }
900        }
901        return bytes;
902}

904protected static String[] readNameTable(String filename) throws java.io.IOException {
905        char[] contents = readTable(filename);
906        char[][] nameAsChar = CharOperation.splitOn('\n', contents);
907 
908        String[] result = new String[nameAsChar.length + 1];
909        result[0] = null;
910        for (int i = 0; i < nameAsChar.length; i++) {
911                result[i + 1] = new String(nameAsChar[i]);
912        }
913 
914        return result;
915}
916protected static String[] readReadableNameTable(String filename) {
917        String[] result = new String[name.length];
918 
919        ResourceBundle bundle;
920        try {
921                bundle = ResourceBundle.getBundle(filename, Locale.getDefault());
922        } catch(MissingResourceException e) {
923                System.out.println("Missing resource : " + filename.replace('.', '/') + ".properties for locale " + Locale.getDefault()); //$NON-NLS-1$//$NON-NLS-2$
924                throw e;
925        }
926        for (int i = 0; i < NT_OFFSET + 1; i++) {
927                result[i] = name[i];
928        }
929        for (int i = NT_OFFSET; i < name.length; i++) {
930                try {
931                        String n = bundle.getString(name[i]);
932                        if(n != null && n.length() > 0) {
933                                result[i] = n;
934                        } else {
935                                result[i] = name[i];
936                        }
937                } catch(MissingResourceException e) {
938                        result[i] = name[i];
939                }
940        }
941        return result;
942}
943protected static char[] readTable(String filename) throws java.io.IOException {
944 
945        //files are located at Parser.class directory
946 
947        InputStream stream = Parser.class.getResourceAsStream(filename);
948        if (stream == null) {
949                throw new java.io.IOException(Messages.bind(Messages.parser_missingFile, filename));
950        }
951        byte[] bytes = null;
952        try {
953                stream = new BufferedInputStream(stream);
954                bytes = Util.getInputStreamAsByteArray(stream, -1);
955        } finally {
956                try {
957                        stream.close();
958                } catch (IOException e) {
959                        // ignore
960                }
961        }
962 
963        //minimal integrity check (even size expected)
964        int length = bytes.length;
965        if ((length & 1) != 0)
966                throw new java.io.IOException(Messages.bind(Messages.parser_corruptedFile, filename));
967 
968        // convert bytes into chars
969        char[] chars = new char[length / 2];
970        int i = 0;
971        int charIndex = 0;
972 
973        while (true) {
974                chars[charIndex++] = (char) (((bytes[i++] & 0xFF) << 8) + (bytes[i++] & 0xFF));
975                if (i == length)
976                        break;
977        }
978        return chars;
979}
980protected static long[] readLongTable(String filename) throws java.io.IOException {
981 
982        //files are located at Parser.class directory
983 
984        InputStream stream = Parser.class.getResourceAsStream(filename);
985        if (stream == null) {
986                throw new java.io.IOException(Messages.bind(Messages.parser_missingFile, filename));
987        }
988        byte[] bytes = null;
989        try {
990                stream = new BufferedInputStream(stream);
991                bytes = Util.getInputStreamAsByteArray(stream, -1);
992        } finally {
993                try {
994                        stream.close();
995                } catch (IOException e) {
996                        // ignore
997                }
998        }
999 
1000        //minimal integrity check (even size expected)
1001        int length = bytes.length;
1002        if (length % 8 != 0)
1003                throw new java.io.IOException(Messages.bind(Messages.parser_corruptedFile, filename));
1004 
1005        // convert bytes into longs
1006        long[] longs = new long[length / 8];
1007        int i = 0;
1008        int longIndex = 0;
1009 
1010        while (true) {
1011                longs[longIndex++] =
1012                  (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 56)
1013                + (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 48)
1014                + (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 40)
1015                + (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 32)
1016                + (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 24)
1017                + (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 16)
1018                + (((long) (bytes[i++] & 0xFF)) << 8)
1019                + (bytes[i++] & 0xFF);
1020 
1021                if (i == length)
1022                        break;
1023        }
1024        return longs;
1025}
1026public static int tAction(int state, int sym) {

1028}

1050protected void annotationRecoveryCheckPoint(int start, int end) {
1051        if(this.lastCheckPoint > start && this.lastCheckPoint < end) {
1052                this.lastCheckPoint = end + 1;
1053        }
1054}
1055public void arrayInitializer(int length) {
1056        //length is the size of the array Initializer
1057        //expressionPtr points on the last elt of the arrayInitializer,
1058        // in other words, it has not been decremented yet.
1059 
1060        ArrayInitializer ai = new ArrayInitializer();
1061        if (length != 0) {
1062                this.expressionPtr -= length;
1063                System.arraycopy(this.expressionStack, this.expressionPtr + 1, ai.expressions = new Expression[length], 0, length);
1064        }
1065        pushOnExpressionStack(ai);
1066        //positionning
1067        ai.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
1068        ai.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
1069}
1070protected void blockReal() {
1071        // See consumeLocalVariableDeclarationStatement in case of change: duplicated code
1072        // increment the amount of declared variables for this block
1073        this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr]++;
1074}
1075/*
1076 * Build initial recovery state.
1077 * Recovery state is inferred from the current state of the parser (reduced node stack).
1078 */
1079public RecoveredElement buildInitialRecoveryState(){
1080 
1081        /* initialize recovery by retrieving available reduced nodes
1082         * also rebuild bracket balance
1083         */
1084        this.lastCheckPoint = 0;
1085        this.lastErrorEndPositionBeforeRecovery = this.scanner.currentPosition;
1086 
1087        RecoveredElement element = null;
1088        if (this.referenceContext instanceof CompilationUnitDeclaration){
1089                if (!DO_DIET_PARSE)
1090                {
1091                        this.methodRecoveryActivated=true;
1092//                        this.statementRecoveryActivated=true;
1093                }
1094                element = new RecoveredUnit(this.compilationUnit, 0, this);
1095 
1096                /* ignore current stack state, since restarting from the beginnning
1097                   since could not trust simple brace count */
1098                if (false){ // experimenting restart recovery from scratch
1099                        this.compilationUnit.currentPackage = null;
1100                        this.compilationUnit.imports = null;
1101                        this.compilationUnit.types = null;
1102                        this.compilationUnit.statements = null;
1103                        this.currentToken = 0;
1104                        this.listLength = 0;
1105                        this.listTypeParameterLength = 0;
1106                        this.endPosition = 0;
1107                        this.endStatementPosition = 0;
1108                        return element;
1109                }
1110                else
1111                {
1112                        this.currentToken = 0;
1113//                        if (this.astPtr<0&&this.compilationUnit.sourceEnd>0)
1114//                                this.lastCheckPoint = this.compilationUnit.sourceEnd;
1115 
1116                }
1117 
1118                if (this.compilationUnit.currentPackage != null){
1119                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.compilationUnit.currentPackage.declarationSourceEnd+1;
1120                }
1121                if (this.compilationUnit.imports != null){
1122                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.compilationUnit.imports[this.compilationUnit.imports.length -1].declarationSourceEnd+1;
1123                }
1124        } else {
1125                if (this.referenceContext instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration){
1126                        element = new RecoveredMethod((AbstractMethodDeclaration) this.referenceContext, null, 0, this);
1127                        this.lastCheckPoint = ((AbstractMethodDeclaration) this.referenceContext).bodyStart;
1128                        if(this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
1129                                element = element.add(new Block(0), 0);
1130                        }
1131                } else {
1132                        /* Initializer bodies are parsed in the context of the type declaration, we must thus search it inside */
1133                        if (this.referenceContext instanceof TypeDeclaration){
1134                                TypeDeclaration type = (TypeDeclaration) this.referenceContext;
1135                                for (int i = 0; i < type.fields.length; i++){
1136                                        FieldDeclaration field = type.fields[i];
1137                                        if (field != null
1138                                                && field.getKind() == AbstractVariableDeclaration.INITIALIZER
1139                                                && field.declarationSourceStart <= this.scanner.initialPosition
1140                                                && this.scanner.initialPosition <= field.declarationSourceEnd
1141                                                && this.scanner.eofPosition <= field.declarationSourceEnd+1){
1142                                                element = new RecoveredInitializer(field, null, 1, this);
1143                                                this.lastCheckPoint = field.declarationSourceStart;
1144                                                break;
1145                                        }
1146                                }
1147                        }
1148                }
1149        }
1150 
1151        if (element == null) return element;
1152 
1153        element = recoverAST(element);
1154        if (this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
1155                if (this.pendingRecoveredType != null &&
1156                                this.scanner.startPosition - 1 <= this.pendingRecoveredType.declarationSourceEnd) {
1157                        // Add the pending type to the AST if this type isn't already added in the AST.
1158                        element = element.add(this.pendingRecoveredType, 0);
1159                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.pendingRecoveredType.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1160                        this.pendingRecoveredType = null;
1161                }
1162        }
1163        ProgramElement[] compUnitStatments = this.compilationUnit.statements;
1164        if (compUnitStatments!=null && compUnitStatments.length>0 &&
1165                        this.lastCheckPoint<compUnitStatments[compUnitStatments.length-1].sourceEnd)
1166        {
1167                ProgramElement programElement = compUnitStatments[compUnitStatments.length-1];
1168 
1169                this.lastCheckPoint=((programElement instanceof Expression) ? ((Expression)programElement).statementEnd : programElement.sourceEnd)+1;
1170        }
1171        return element;
1172}
1173 
1174public RecoveredElement recoverAST(RecoveredElement element) {
1175        for(int i = 0; i <= this.astPtr; i++){
1176                ASTNode node = this.astStack[i];
1177                if (node instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration){
1178                        AbstractMethodDeclaration method = (AbstractMethodDeclaration) node;
1179                        if (method.selector!=null)
1180                        {
1181                                if (method.declarationSourceEnd == 0){
1182                                        element = element.add(method, 0);
1183                                        this.lastCheckPoint = method.bodyStart;
1184                                } else {
1185                                        element = element.add(method, 0);
1186                                        this.lastCheckPoint = method.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1187                                }
1188                        }
1189                        else
1190                                element = recoverFunctionExpression(element,method);
1191                        continue;
1192                }
1193                if (node instanceof Initializer){
1194                        Initializer initializer = (Initializer) node;
1195                        if (initializer.declarationSourceEnd == 0){
1196                                element = element.add(initializer, 1);
1197                                this.lastCheckPoint = initializer.sourceStart;
1198                        } else {
1199                                element = element.add(initializer, 0);
1200                                this.lastCheckPoint = initializer.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1201                        }
1202                        continue;
1203                }
1204                if (node instanceof FieldDeclaration){
1205                        FieldDeclaration field = (FieldDeclaration) node;
1206                        if (field.declarationSourceEnd == 0){
1207                                element = element.add(field, 0);
1208                                if (field.initialization == null){
1209                                        this.lastCheckPoint = field.sourceEnd + 1;
1210                                } else {
1211                                        this.lastCheckPoint = field.initialization.sourceEnd + 1;
1212                                }
1213                        } else {
1214                                element = element.add(field, 0);
1215                                this.lastCheckPoint = field.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1216                        }
1217                        continue;
1218                }
1219                if (node instanceof LocalDeclaration){
1220                        LocalDeclaration localDecl = (LocalDeclaration) node;
1221                        if (localDecl.declarationSourceEnd == 0){
1222                                element = element.add(localDecl, 0);
1223                                if (localDecl.initialization == null){
1224                                        this.lastCheckPoint = localDecl.sourceEnd + 1;
1225                                } else {
1226                                        this.lastCheckPoint = localDecl.initialization.sourceEnd + 1;
1227                                }
1228                        } else {
1229                                element = element.add(localDecl, 0);
1230                                this.lastCheckPoint = localDecl.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1231                        }
1232                        continue;
1233                }
1234                if (node instanceof TypeDeclaration){
1235                        TypeDeclaration type = (TypeDeclaration) node;
1236                        if (type.declarationSourceEnd == 0){
1237                                element = element.add(type, 0);
1238                                this.lastCheckPoint = type.bodyStart;
1239                        } else {
1240                                element = element.add(type, 0);
1241                                this.lastCheckPoint = type.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1242                        }
1243                        continue;
1244                }
1245                if (node instanceof Statement){
1246                        Statement statement = (Statement) node;
1247                        if (statement.sourceEnd == 0){
1248                                element = element.add(statement, 1);
1249                                this.lastCheckPoint = statement.sourceStart;
1250                        } else {
1251                                element = element.add(statement, 0);
1252                                this.lastCheckPoint = statement.sourceEnd + 1;
1253                        }
1254                        continue;
1255                }
1256                if (node instanceof ImportReference){
1257                        ImportReference importRef = (ImportReference) node;
1258                        element = element.add(importRef, 0);
1259                        this.lastCheckPoint = importRef.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1260                }
1261                if(this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
1262                        if(node instanceof Block) {
1263                                Block block = (Block) node;
1264                                element = element.add(block, 0);
1265                                this.lastCheckPoint = block.sourceEnd + 1;
1266                        } else if(node instanceof LocalDeclaration) {
1267                                LocalDeclaration statement = (LocalDeclaration) node;
1268                                element = element.add(statement, 0);
1269                                this.lastCheckPoint = statement.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1270                        } else if(node instanceof Expression) {
1271                                if(node instanceof Assignment ||
1272                                                node instanceof PrefixExpression ||
1273                                                node instanceof PostfixExpression ||
1274                                                node instanceof MessageSend ||
1275                                                node instanceof AllocationExpression) {
1276                                        // recover only specific expressions
1277                                        Expression statement = (Expression) node;
1278                                        element = element.add(statement, 0);
1279                                        if(statement.statementEnd != -1) {
1280                                                this.lastCheckPoint = statement.statementEnd + 1;
1281                                        } else {
1282                                                this.lastCheckPoint = statement.sourceEnd + 1;
1283                                        }
1284                                }
1285                        } else if(node instanceof Statement) {
1286                                Statement statement = (Statement) node;
1287                                element = element.add(statement, 0);
1288                                this.lastCheckPoint = statement.sourceEnd + 1;
1289                        }
1290                }
1291        }
1292        return element;
1293}
1294 
1295protected RecoveredElement recoverFunctionExpression(RecoveredElement element, AbstractMethodDeclaration method) {
1296        int start = method.exprStackPtr;
1297//        int end=this.expressionPtr;
1298        boolean isAssignment=true;
1299        Statement expression=null;
1300 
1301    FunctionExpression funcExpr=new FunctionExpression((MethodDeclaration)method);
1302    funcExpr.sourceEnd=method.declarationSourceEnd;
1303    funcExpr.sourceStart=method.sourceStart;
1304 
1305 
1306        if (isAssignment && start>=0)
1307        {
1308                expression=new Assignment(this.expressionStack[start],funcExpr,method.declarationSourceEnd);
1309        }
1310        if (expression!=null)
1311        {
1312                element = element.add(expression, 1);
1313                if (method.declarationSourceEnd == 0){
1314                        element = element.add(method, 0);
1315                        this.lastCheckPoint = method.bodyStart;
1316                } else {
1317                        element = element.add(method, 0);
1318                        this.lastCheckPoint = method.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
1319                }
1320                if (element instanceof RecoveredMethod)
1321                        element.add(new Block(0), 0);
1322        }
1323 
1324        return element;
1325}
1326protected void checkAndSetModifiers(int flag){
1327        /*modify the current modifiers buffer.
1328        When the startPosition of the modifiers is 0
1329        it means that the modifier being parsed is the first
1330        of a list of several modifiers. The startPosition
1331        is zeroed when a copy of modifiers-buffer is push
1332        onto the this.astStack. */
1333 
1334        if ((this.modifiers & flag) != 0){ // duplicate modifier
1335                this.modifiers |= ExtraCompilerModifiers.AccAlternateModifierProblem;
1336        }
1337        this.modifiers |= flag;
1338 
1339        if (this.modifiersSourceStart < 0) this.modifiersSourceStart = this.scanner.startPosition;
1340}
1341public void checkComment() {
1342 
1343        // discard obsolete comments while inside methods or fields initializer (see bug 74369)
1344        if (!(this.diet && this.dietInt==0) && this.scanner.commentPtr >= 0) {
1345                flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
1346        }
1347 
1348        int lastComment = this.scanner.commentPtr;
1349 
1350//        if (this.modifiersSourceStart >= 0) {
1351//                // eliminate comments located after modifierSourceStart if positionned
1352//                while (lastComment >= 0 && this.scanner.commentStarts[lastComment] > this.modifiersSourceStart) lastComment--;
1353//        }
1354        if (lastComment >= 0) {
1355                // consider all remaining leading comments to be part of current declaration
1356                this.modifiersSourceStart = this.scanner.commentStarts[0];
1357 
1358                // check deprecation in last comment if javadoc (can be followed by non-javadoc comments which are simply ignored)
1359                while (lastComment >= 0 && this.scanner.commentStops[lastComment] < 0) lastComment--; // non javadoc comment have negative end positions
1360                if (lastComment >= 0 && this.javadocParser != null) {
1361                        int commentEnd = this.scanner.commentStops[lastComment] - 1; //stop is one over,
1362                        // do not report problem before last parsed comment while recovering code...
1363                        this.javadocParser.reportProblems = this.currentElement == null || commentEnd > this.lastJavadocEnd;
1364                        if (this.javadocParser.checkDeprecation(lastComment)) {
1365                                checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccDeprecated);
1366                        }
1367                        this.javadoc = this.javadocParser.docComment;        // null if check javadoc is not activated
1368                        if (currentElement == null) this.lastJavadocEnd = commentEnd;
1369                }
1370        }
1371}
1372protected void checkNonNLSAfterBodyEnd(int declarationEnd){
1373        if(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1 <= declarationEnd) {
1374                this.scanner.eofPosition = declarationEnd < Integer.MAX_VALUE ? declarationEnd + 1 : declarationEnd;
1375                try {
1376                        while(this.scanner.getNextToken() != TokenNameEOF){/*empty*/}
1377                } catch (InvalidInputException e) {
1378                        // Nothing to do
1379                }
1380        }

1446protected void concatGenericsLists() {
1447        this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr - 1] += this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr--];

1449protected void concatNodeLists() {
1450        /*
1451         * This is a case where you have two sublists into the this.astStack that you want
1452         * to merge in one list. There is no action required on the this.astStack. The only
1453         * thing you need to do is merge the two lengths specified on the astStackLength.
1454         * The top two length are for example:
1455         * ... p   n
1456         * and you want to result in a list like:
1457         * ... n+p
1458         * This means that the p could be equals to 0 in case there is no astNode pushed
1459         * on the this.astStack.
1460         * Look at the InterfaceMemberDeclarations for an example.
1461         */
1462 
1463        this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr - 1] += this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--];
1464}

1478protected void consumeAllocationHeader() {
1479        // ClassInstanceCreationExpression ::= 'new' ClassType '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ClassBodyopt
1480 
1481        // ClassBodyopt produces a null item on the astStak if it produces NO class body
1482        // An empty class body produces a 0 on the length stack.....
1483 
1484        if (this.currentElement == null){
1485                return; // should never occur, this consumeRule is only used in recovery mode
1486        }
1487        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameLBRACE){
1488                // beginning of an anonymous type
1489                TypeDeclaration anonymousType = new TypeDeclaration(this.compilationUnit.compilationResult);
1490                anonymousType.name =CharOperation.NO_CHAR;
1491                anonymousType.bits |= (ASTNode.IsAnonymousType|ASTNode.IsLocalType);
1492                anonymousType.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
1493                anonymousType.sourceEnd = this.rParenPos; // closing parenthesis
1494                QualifiedAllocationExpression alloc = new QualifiedAllocationExpression(anonymousType);
1495                alloc.type = getTypeReference(0);
1496                alloc.sourceStart = anonymousType.sourceStart;
1497                alloc.sourceEnd = anonymousType.sourceEnd ;
1498                this.lastCheckPoint = anonymousType.bodyStart = this.scanner.currentPosition;
1499                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(anonymousType, 0);
1500                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
1501                this.currentToken = 0; // opening brace already taken into account
1502                return;
1503        }
1504        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.startPosition; // force to restart at this exact position
1505        this.restartRecovery = true; // request to restart from here on
1506}
1507protected void consumeAnnotationAsModifier() {
1508        Expression expression = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
1509        int sourceStart = expression.sourceStart;
1510        if (this.modifiersSourceStart < 0) {
1511                this.modifiersSourceStart = sourceStart;
1512        }
1513}
1514protected void consumeAnnotationName() {
1515        if(this.currentElement != null) {
1516                int start = this.intStack[this.intPtr];
1517                int end = (int) (this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr] & 0x00000000FFFFFFFFL);
1518                annotationRecoveryCheckPoint(start, end);
1519        }
1520        this.recordStringLiterals = false;
1521}
1522protected void consumeAnnotationTypeDeclaration() {
1523        int length;
1524        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
1525                //there are length declarations
1526                //dispatch according to the type of the declarations
1527                dispatchDeclarationInto(length);
1528        }
1529 
1530        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
1531 
1532        // mark initializers with local type mark if needed
1533        markInitializersWithLocalType(typeDecl);
1534 
1535        //convert constructor that do not have the type's name into methods
1536        typeDecl.checkConstructors(this);
1537 
1538        //always add <clinit> (will be remove at code gen time if empty)
1539        if (this.scanner.containsAssertKeyword) {
1540                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.ContainsAssertion;
1541        }
1542        typeDecl.addClinit();
1543        typeDecl.bodyEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
1544        if (length == 0 && !containsComment(typeDecl.bodyStart, typeDecl.bodyEnd)) {
1545                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
1546        }
1547        typeDecl.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
1548}

1552        }
1553        // flush the comments related to the annotation type header
1554        this.scanner.commentPtr = -1;
1555}

1569protected void consumeArrayAccess(boolean unspecifiedReference) {
1570        // ArrayAccess ::= Name '[' Expression ']' ==> true
1571        // ArrayAccess ::= PrimaryNoNewArray '[' Expression ']' ==> false
1572 
1573 
1574        //optimize push/pop
1575        Expression exp;
1576        if (unspecifiedReference) {
1577                exp =
1578                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1579                                new ArrayReference(
1580                                        getUnspecifiedReferenceOptimized(),
1581                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr]);
1582        } else {
1583                this.expressionPtr--;
1584                this.expressionLengthPtr--;
1585                exp =
1586                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1587                                new ArrayReference(
1588                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr],
1589                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr + 1]);
1590        }
1591        exp.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
1592}
1593protected void consumeArrayCreationExpressionWithInitializer() {

1595        // ArrayCreationWithArrayInitializer ::= 'new' ClassOrInterfaceType DimWithOrWithOutExprs ArrayInitializer
1596 
1597        int length;
1598        ArrayAllocationExpression arrayAllocation = new ArrayAllocationExpression();
1599        this.expressionLengthPtr -- ;
1600        arrayAllocation.initializer = (ArrayInitializer) this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--];
1601 
1602        arrayAllocation.type = getTypeReference(0);
1603        arrayAllocation.type.bits |= ASTNode.IgnoreRawTypeCheck; // no need to worry about raw type usage
1604        length = (this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]);
1605        this.expressionPtr -= length ;
1606        System.arraycopy(
1607                this.expressionStack,
1608                this.expressionPtr+1,
1609                arrayAllocation.dimensions = new Expression[length],
1610                0,
1611                length);

1613        if (arrayAllocation.initializer == null) {
1614                arrayAllocation.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
1615        } else {
1616                arrayAllocation.sourceEnd = arrayAllocation.initializer.sourceEnd ;
1617        }
1618        pushOnExpressionStack(arrayAllocation);
1619}

1657protected void consumeAssignment() {
1658        // Assignment ::= LeftHandSide AssignmentOperator AssignmentExpression
1659        //optimize the push/pop
1660 
1661        int op = this.intStack[this.intPtr--] ; //<--the encoded operator
1662 
1663        this.expressionPtr -- ; this.expressionLengthPtr -- ;
1664        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1665                (op != EQUAL ) ?
1666                        new CompoundAssignment(
1667                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] ,
1668                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr+1],
1669                                op,
1670                                this.scanner.startPosition - 1)        :
1671                        new Assignment(
1672                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] ,
1673                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr+1],
1674                                this.scanner.startPosition - 1);
1675 
1676                                if (this.pendingRecoveredType != null) {
1677                                        // Used only in statements recovery.
1678                                        // This is not a real assignment but a placeholder for an existing anonymous type.
1679                                        // The assignment must be replace by the anonymous type.
1680                                        if (this.pendingRecoveredType.allocation != null &&
1681                                                        this.scanner.startPosition - 1 <= this.pendingRecoveredType.declarationSourceEnd) {
1682                                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = this.pendingRecoveredType.allocation;
1683                                                this.pendingRecoveredType = null;
1684                                                return;
1685                                        }
1686                                        this.pendingRecoveredType = null;
1687                                }
1688}
1689protected void consumeAssignmentOperator(int pos) {
1690        // AssignmentOperator ::= '='
1691        // AssignmentOperator ::= '*='
1692        // AssignmentOperator ::= '/='
1693        // AssignmentOperator ::= '%='
1694        // AssignmentOperator ::= '+='
1695        // AssignmentOperator ::= '-='
1696        // AssignmentOperator ::= '<<='
1697        // AssignmentOperator ::= '>>='
1698        // AssignmentOperator ::= '>>>='
1699        // AssignmentOperator ::= '&='
1700        // AssignmentOperator ::= '^='
1701        // AssignmentOperator ::= '|='
1702

1705protected void consumeBinaryExpression(int op) {
1706        // MultiplicativeExpression ::= MultiplicativeExpression '*' UnaryExpression
1707        // MultiplicativeExpression ::= MultiplicativeExpression '/' UnaryExpression
1708        // MultiplicativeExpression ::= MultiplicativeExpression '%' UnaryExpression
1709        // AdditiveExpression ::= AdditiveExpression '+' MultiplicativeExpression
1710        // AdditiveExpression ::= AdditiveExpression '-' MultiplicativeExpression
1711        // ShiftExpression ::= ShiftExpression '<<'  AdditiveExpression
1712        // ShiftExpression ::= ShiftExpression '>>'  AdditiveExpression
1713        // ShiftExpression ::= ShiftExpression '>>>' AdditiveExpression
1714        // RelationalExpression ::= RelationalExpression '<'  ShiftExpression
1715        // RelationalExpression ::= RelationalExpression '>'  ShiftExpression
1716        // RelationalExpression ::= RelationalExpression '<=' ShiftExpression
1717        // RelationalExpression ::= RelationalExpression '>=' ShiftExpression
1718        // AndExpression ::= AndExpression '&' EqualityExpression
1719        // ExclusiveOrExpression ::= ExclusiveOrExpression '^' AndExpression
1720        // InclusiveOrExpression ::= InclusiveOrExpression '|' ExclusiveOrExpression
1721        // ConditionalAndExpression ::= ConditionalAndExpression '&&' InclusiveOrExpression
1722        // ConditionalOrExpression ::= ConditionalOrExpression '||' ConditionalAndExpression
1723 
1724        //optimize the push/pop
1725 
1726        this.expressionPtr--;
1727        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
1728        Expression expr1 = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
1729        Expression expr2 = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr + 1];
1730        switch(op) {
1731                case OR_OR :
1732                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1733                                new OR_OR_Expression(
1734                                        expr1,
1735                                        expr2,
1736                                        op);
1737                        break;
1738                case AND_AND :
1739                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1740                                new AND_AND_Expression(
1741                                        expr1,
1742                                        expr2,
1743                                        op);
1744                        break;
1745                case PLUS :
1746                        // look for "string1" + "string2"
1747                        // look for "string1" + "string2"
1748                        if (this.optimizeStringLiterals) {
1749                                if (expr1 instanceof StringLiteral) {
1750                                        if (expr2 instanceof CharLiteral) { // string+char
1751                                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1752                                                        ((StringLiteral) expr1).extendWith((CharLiteral) expr2);
1753                                        } else if (expr2 instanceof StringLiteral) { //string+string
1754                                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1755                                                        ((StringLiteral) expr1).extendWith((StringLiteral) expr2);
1756                                        } else {
1757                                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = new BinaryExpression(expr1, expr2, PLUS);
1758                                        }
1759                                } else if (expr1 instanceof CombinedBinaryExpression) {
1760                                        CombinedBinaryExpression cursor;
1761                                        // left branch is comprised of PLUS BEs
1762                                        // cursor is shifted upwards, while needed BEs are added
1763                                        // on demand; past the arityMax-th
1764                                        // consecutive BE, a CBE is inserted that holds a
1765                                        // full-fledged references table
1766                                        if ((cursor = (CombinedBinaryExpression)expr1).arity <
1767                                                                cursor.arityMax) {
1768                                                cursor.left = new BinaryExpression(cursor.left,
1769                                                                cursor.right, PLUS);
1770                                                cursor.arity++;
1771                                        } else {
1772                                                cursor.left = new CombinedBinaryExpression(cursor.left,
1773                                                                cursor.right, PLUS, cursor.arity);
1774                                                cursor.arity = 0;
1775                                                cursor.tuneArityMax();
1776                                        }
1777                                        cursor.right = expr2;
1778                                        cursor.sourceEnd = expr2.sourceEnd;
1779                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = cursor;
1780                                        // BE_INSTRUMENTATION: neutralized in the released code
1781//                                        cursor.depthTracker = ((BinaryExpression)cursor.left).
1782//                                                depthTracker + 1;
1783                                } else if (expr1 instanceof BinaryExpression &&
1784                                                        // single out the a + b case, which is a BE
1785                                                        // instead of a CBE (slightly more than a half of
1786                                                        // strings concatenation are one-deep binary
1787                                                        // expressions)
1788                                                ((expr1.bits & ASTNode.OperatorMASK) >>
1789                                                        ASTNode.OperatorSHIFT) == OperatorIds.PLUS) {
1790                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1791                                                new CombinedBinaryExpression(expr1, expr2, PLUS, 1);
1792                                } else {
1793                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1794                                                new BinaryExpression(expr1, expr2, PLUS);
1795                                }
1796                        } else if (expr1 instanceof StringLiteral) {
1797                                if (expr2 instanceof StringLiteral) {
1798                                        // string + string
1799                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1800                                                ((StringLiteral) expr1).extendsWith((StringLiteral) expr2);
1801                                } else {
1802                                        // single out the a + b case
1803                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1804                                                new BinaryExpression(expr1, expr2, PLUS);
1805                                }
1806                        } else if (expr1 instanceof CombinedBinaryExpression) {
1807                                        CombinedBinaryExpression cursor;
1808                                        // shift cursor; create BE/CBE as needed
1809                                        if ((cursor = (CombinedBinaryExpression)expr1).arity <
1810                                                                cursor.arityMax) {
1811                                                cursor.left = new BinaryExpression(cursor.left,
1812                                                                cursor.right, PLUS);
1813                                                cursor.arity++;
1814                                        } else {
1815                                                cursor.left = new CombinedBinaryExpression(cursor.left,
1816                                                                cursor.right, PLUS, cursor.arity);
1817                                                cursor.arity = 0;
1818                                                cursor.tuneArityMax();
1819                                        }
1820                                        cursor.right = expr2;
1821                                        cursor.sourceEnd = expr2.sourceEnd;
1822                                        // BE_INSTRUMENTATION: neutralized in the released code
1823//                                        cursor.depthTracker = ((BinaryExpression)cursor.left).
1824//                                                depthTracker + 1;
1825                                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = cursor;
1826                        } else if (expr1 instanceof BinaryExpression &&
1827                                                        // single out the a + b case
1828                                                ((expr1.bits & ASTNode.OperatorMASK) >>
1829                                                        ASTNode.OperatorSHIFT) == OperatorIds.PLUS) {
1830                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1831                                        new CombinedBinaryExpression(expr1, expr2, PLUS, 1);
1832                        } else {
1833                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1834                                        new BinaryExpression(expr1, expr2, PLUS);
1835                        }
1836                        break;
1837                case LESS :
1838                        this.intPtr--;
1839                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1840                                new BinaryExpression(
1841                                        expr1,
1842                                        expr2,
1843                                        op);
1844                        break;
1845                default :
1846                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
1847                                new BinaryExpression(
1848                                        expr1,
1849                                        expr2,
1850                                        op);
1851        }
1852}

1974protected void consumeBlock() {
1975        // Block ::= OpenBlock '{' BlockStatementsopt '}'
1976        // simpler action for empty blocks
1977 
1978        int statementsLength = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--];
1979        Block block;
1980        if (statementsLength == 0) { // empty block
1981                block = new Block(0);
1982                block.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
1983                block.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
1984                // check whether this block at least contains some comment in it
1985                if (!containsComment(block.sourceStart, block.sourceEnd)) {
1986                        block.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
1987                }
1988                this.realBlockPtr--; // still need to pop the block variable counter
1989        } else {
1990                block = new Block(this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr--]);
1991                this.astPtr -= statementsLength;
1992                System.arraycopy(
1993                        this.astStack,
1994                        this.astPtr + 1,
1995                        block.statements = new Statement[statementsLength],
1996                        0,
1997                        statementsLength);
1998                block.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
1999                block.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
2000        }
2001        pushOnAstStack(block);
2002}

2077protected ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference computeQualifiedGenericsFromRightSide(TypeReference rightSide, int dim) {
2078        int nameSize = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr];
2079        int tokensSize = nameSize;
2080        if (rightSide instanceof ParameterizedSingleTypeReference) {
2081                tokensSize ++;
2082        } else if (rightSide instanceof SingleTypeReference) {
2083                tokensSize ++;
2084        } else if (rightSide instanceof ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference) {
2085                tokensSize += ((QualifiedTypeReference) rightSide).tokens.length;
2086        } else if (rightSide instanceof QualifiedTypeReference) {
2087                tokensSize += ((QualifiedTypeReference) rightSide).tokens.length;
2088        }
2089        TypeReference[][] typeArguments = new TypeReference[tokensSize][];
2090        char[][] tokens = new char[tokensSize][];
2091        long[] positions = new long[tokensSize];
2092        if (rightSide instanceof ParameterizedSingleTypeReference) {
2093                ParameterizedSingleTypeReference singleParameterizedTypeReference = (ParameterizedSingleTypeReference) rightSide;
2094                tokens[nameSize] = singleParameterizedTypeReference.token;
2095                positions[nameSize] = (((long) singleParameterizedTypeReference.sourceStart) << 32) + singleParameterizedTypeReference.sourceEnd;
2096                typeArguments[nameSize] = singleParameterizedTypeReference.typeArguments;
2097        } else if (rightSide instanceof SingleTypeReference) {
2098                SingleTypeReference singleTypeReference = (SingleTypeReference) rightSide;
2099                tokens[nameSize] = singleTypeReference.token;
2100                positions[nameSize] = (((long) singleTypeReference.sourceStart) << 32) + singleTypeReference.sourceEnd;
2101        } else if (rightSide instanceof ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference) {
2102                ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference parameterizedTypeReference = (ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference) rightSide;
2103                TypeReference[][] rightSideTypeArguments = parameterizedTypeReference.typeArguments;
2104                System.arraycopy(rightSideTypeArguments, 0, typeArguments, nameSize, rightSideTypeArguments.length);
2105                char[][] rightSideTokens = parameterizedTypeReference.tokens;
2106                System.arraycopy(rightSideTokens, 0, tokens, nameSize, rightSideTokens.length);
2107                long[] rightSidePositions = parameterizedTypeReference.sourcePositions;
2108                System.arraycopy(rightSidePositions, 0, positions, nameSize, rightSidePositions.length);
2109        } else if (rightSide instanceof QualifiedTypeReference) {
2110                QualifiedTypeReference qualifiedTypeReference = (QualifiedTypeReference) rightSide;
2111                char[][] rightSideTokens = qualifiedTypeReference.tokens;
2112                System.arraycopy(rightSideTokens, 0, tokens, nameSize, rightSideTokens.length);
2113                long[] rightSidePositions = qualifiedTypeReference.sourcePositions;
2114                System.arraycopy(rightSidePositions, 0, positions, nameSize, rightSidePositions.length);
2115        }
2116 
2117        int currentTypeArgumentsLength = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr--];
2118        TypeReference[] currentTypeArguments = new TypeReference[currentTypeArgumentsLength];
2119        this.genericsPtr -= currentTypeArgumentsLength;
2120        System.arraycopy(this.genericsStack, this.genericsPtr + 1, currentTypeArguments, 0, currentTypeArgumentsLength);
2121 
2122        if (nameSize == 1) {
2123                tokens[0] = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr];
2124                positions[0] = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--];
2125                typeArguments[0] = currentTypeArguments;
2126        } else {
2127                this.identifierPtr -= nameSize;
2128                System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, nameSize);
2129                System.arraycopy(this.identifierPositionStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, positions, 0, nameSize);
2130                typeArguments[nameSize - 1] = currentTypeArguments;
2131        }
2132        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
2133        return new ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference(tokens, typeArguments, dim, positions);
2134}
2135protected void consumeCastExpressionWithQualifiedGenericsArray() {
2136        // CastExpression ::= PushLPAREN Name OnlyTypeArguments '.' ClassOrInterfaceType Dims PushRPAREN InsideCastExpression UnaryExpressionNotPlusMinus
2137        Expression exp, cast, castType;
2138        int end = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2139 
2140        int dim = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2141        TypeReference rightSide = getTypeReference(0);
2142 
2143        ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference qualifiedParameterizedTypeReference = computeQualifiedGenericsFromRightSide(rightSide, dim);
2144        intPtr--;
2145        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = cast = new CastExpression(exp = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr], castType = qualifiedParameterizedTypeReference);
2146        castType.sourceEnd = end - 1;
2147        castType.sourceStart = (cast.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--]) + 1;
2148        cast.sourceEnd = exp.sourceEnd;
2149}

2154protected void consumeCatchHeader() {
2155        // CatchDeclaration ::= 'catch' '(' FormalParameter ')' '{'
2156 
2157        if (this.currentElement == null){
2158                return; // should never occur, this consumeRule is only used in recovery mode
2159        }
2160        // current element should be a block due to the presence of the opening brace
2161        if (!(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredBlock)){
2162                if(!(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredMethod)) {
2163                        return;
2164                }
2165                RecoveredMethod rMethod = (RecoveredMethod) this.currentElement;
2166                if(!(rMethod.methodBody == null && rMethod.bracketBalance > 0)) {
2167                        return;
2168                }
2169        }
2170 
2171        Argument arg = (Argument)this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
2172        // convert argument to local variable
2173        LocalDeclaration localDeclaration = new LocalDeclaration(arg.name, arg.sourceStart, arg.sourceEnd);
2174        localDeclaration.type = arg.type;
2175        localDeclaration.declarationSourceStart = arg.declarationSourceStart;
2176        localDeclaration.declarationSourceEnd = arg.declarationSourceEnd;
2177 
2178        this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(localDeclaration, 0);
2179        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.startPosition; // force to restart at this exact position
2180        this.restartRecovery = true; // request to restart from here on
2181        this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
2182}
2183protected void consumeClassBodyDeclaration() {
2184        // ClassBodyDeclaration ::= Diet Block
2185        //push an Initializer
2186        //optimize the push/pop
2187        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]--;
2188        Block block = (Block) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2189        if (this.diet) block.bits &= ~ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock; // clear bit since was diet
2190        Initializer initializer = new Initializer(block, 0);
2191        this.intPtr--; // pop sourcestart left on the stack by consumeNestedMethod.
2192        initializer.bodyStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2193        this.realBlockPtr--; // pop the block variable counter left on the stack by consumeNestedMethod
2194        int javadocCommentStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2195        if (javadocCommentStart != -1) {
2196                initializer.declarationSourceStart = javadocCommentStart;
2197                initializer.javadoc = this.javadoc;
2198                this.javadoc = null;
2199        }
2200        this.astStack[this.astPtr] = initializer;
2201        initializer.bodyEnd = this.endPosition;
2202        initializer.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
2203        initializer.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
2204}
