2221protected void consumeClassDeclaration() {
2222        // ClassDeclaration ::= ClassHeader ClassBody
2223 
2224        int length;
2225        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
2226                //there are length declarations
2227                //dispatch according to the type of the declarations
2228                dispatchDeclarationInto(length);
2229        }
2230 
2231        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2232 
2233        // mark initializers with local type mark if needed
2234        markInitializersWithLocalType(typeDecl);
2235 
2236        //convert constructor that do not have the type's name into methods
2237        boolean hasConstructor = typeDecl.checkConstructors(this);
2238 
2239        //add the default constructor when needed (interface don't have it)
2240        if (!hasConstructor) {
2241                switch(TypeDeclaration.kind(typeDecl.modifiers)) {
2242                        case TypeDeclaration.CLASS_DECL :
2243                        case TypeDeclaration.ENUM_DECL :
2244                                boolean insideFieldInitializer = false;
2245                                if (this.diet) {
2246                                        for (int i = this.nestedType; i > 0; i--){
2247                                                if (this.variablesCounter[i] > 0) {
2248                                                        insideFieldInitializer = true;
2249                                                        break;
2250                                                }
2251                                        }
2252                                }
2253                                typeDecl.createDefaultConstructor(!this.diet || insideFieldInitializer, true);
2254                }
2255        }
2256        //always add <clinit> (will be remove at code gen time if empty)
2257        if (this.scanner.containsAssertKeyword) {
2258                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.ContainsAssertion;
2259        }
2260        typeDecl.addClinit();
2261        typeDecl.bodyEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
2262        if (length == 0 && !containsComment(typeDecl.bodyStart, typeDecl.bodyEnd)) {
2263                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
2264        }
2265 
2266        typeDecl.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
2267}
2268protected void consumeClassHeader() {
2269        // ClassHeader ::= ClassHeaderName ClassHeaderExtendsopt ClassHeaderImplementsopt
2270 
2271        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2272        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameLBRACE) {
2273                typeDecl.bodyStart = this.scanner.currentPosition;
2274        }
2275        if (this.currentElement != null) {
2276                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
2277        }
2278        // flush the comments related to the class header
2279        this.scanner.commentPtr = -1;
2280}
2281protected void consumeClassHeaderExtends() {

2283        //superclass

2285        // There is a class declaration on the top of stack
2286        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2287        typeDecl.superclass = superClass;
2288        superClass.bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;

2295protected void consumeClassHeaderImplements() {
2296        // ClassHeaderImplements ::= 'implements' InterfaceTypeList
2297        int length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--];
2298        //super interfaces
2299        this.astPtr -= length;
2300        // There is a class declaration on the top of stack
2301        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2302        System.arraycopy(
2303                this.astStack,
2304                this.astPtr + 1,
2305                typeDecl.superInterfaces = new TypeReference[length],
2306                0,
2307                length);
2308        for (int i = 0, max = typeDecl.superInterfaces.length; i < max; i++) {
2309                typeDecl.superInterfaces[i].bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
2310        }
2311        typeDecl.bodyStart = typeDecl.superInterfaces[length-1].sourceEnd + 1;
2312        this.listLength = 0; // reset after having read super-interfaces
2313        // recovery
2314        if (this.currentElement != null) { // is recovering
2315                this.lastCheckPoint = typeDecl.bodyStart;
2316        }

2318protected void consumeClassHeaderName1() {
2319        // ClassHeaderName1 ::= Modifiersopt 'class' 'Identifier'
2320        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = new TypeDeclaration(this.compilationUnit.compilationResult);
2321        if (this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType] == 0) {
2322                if (this.nestedType != 0) {
2323                        typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.IsMemberType;
2324                }
2325        } else {
2326                // Record that the block has a declaration for local types
2327                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.IsLocalType;
2328                markEnclosingMemberWithLocalType();
2329                blockReal();
2330        }
2331 
2332        //highlight the name of the type
2333        long pos = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr];
2334        typeDecl.sourceEnd = (int) pos;
2335        typeDecl.sourceStart = (int) (pos >>> 32);
2336        typeDecl.name = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr--];
2337        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
2338 
2339        //compute the declaration source too
2340        // 'class' and 'interface' push two int positions: the beginning of the class token and its end.
2341        // we want to keep the beginning position but get rid of the end position
2342        // it is only used for the ClassLiteralAccess positions.
2343        typeDecl.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2344        this.intPtr--; // remove the end position of the class token
2345 
2346        typeDecl.modifiersSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2347        typeDecl.modifiers = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2348        if (typeDecl.modifiersSourceStart >= 0) {
2349                typeDecl.declarationSourceStart = typeDecl.modifiersSourceStart;
2350        }
2351 
2352        // Store secondary info
2353        if ((typeDecl.bits & ASTNode.IsMemberType) == 0 && (typeDecl.bits & ASTNode.IsLocalType) == 0) {
2354                if (this.compilationUnit != null && !CharOperation.equals(typeDecl.name, this.compilationUnit.getMainTypeName())) {
2355                        typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.IsSecondaryType;
2356                }
2357        }
2358        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
2359 
2360        typeDecl.bodyStart = typeDecl.sourceEnd + 1;
2361        pushOnAstStack(typeDecl);
2362 
2363        this.listLength = 0; // will be updated when reading super-interfaces
2364        // recovery
2365        if (this.currentElement != null){
2366                this.lastCheckPoint = typeDecl.bodyStart;
2367                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(typeDecl, 0);
2368                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
2369        }
2370        // javadoc
2371        typeDecl.javadoc = this.javadoc;
2372        this.javadoc = null;
2373}
2374protected void consumeTypeHeaderNameWithTypeParameters() {
2375        // ClassHeaderName ::= ClassHeaderName1 TypeParameters
2376        // InterfaceHeaderName ::= InterfaceHeaderName1 TypeParameters
2377        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration)this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2378

2383

2385

2387

2428        if (((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) == 1) && (this.astStack[this.astPtr] == null)) {

2565protected void consumeConditionalExpression(int op) {
2566        // ConditionalExpression ::= ConditionalOrExpression '?' Expression ':' ConditionalExpression
2567        //optimize the push/pop
2568        this.intPtr -= 2;//consume position of the question mark
2569        this.expressionPtr -= 2;
2570        this.expressionLengthPtr -= 2;
2571        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
2572                new ConditionalExpression(
2573                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr],
2574                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr + 1],
2575                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr + 2]);
2576}
2577/**
2578 * @param op
2579 */
2580protected void consumeConditionalExpressionWithName(int op) {
2581        // ConditionalExpression ::= Name '?' Expression ':' ConditionalExpression
2582        this.intPtr -= 2;//consume position of the question mark
2583        pushOnExpressionStack(getUnspecifiedReferenceOptimized());
2584        this.expressionPtr -= 2;
2585        this.expressionLengthPtr -= 2;
2586        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
2587                new ConditionalExpression(
2588                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr + 2],
2589                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr],
2590                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr + 1]);

2596protected void consumeConstructorBody() {

2600}
2601protected void consumeConstructorDeclaration() {
2602        // ConstructorDeclaration ::= ConstructorHeader ConstructorBody
2603 
2604        /*
2605        this.astStack : FunctionDeclaration statements
2606        this.identifierStack : name
2607         ==>
2608        this.astStack : FunctionDeclaration
2609        this.identifierStack :
2610        */
2611 
2612        //must provide a default constructor call when needed
2613 
2614        int length;
2615 
2616        // pop the position of the {  (body of the method) pushed in block decl
2617        this.intPtr--;
2618        this.intPtr--;
2619 
2620        //statements
2621        this.realBlockPtr--;
2622        ExplicitConstructorCall constructorCall = null;
2623        Statement[] statements = null;
2624        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
2625                this.astPtr -= length;
2626                if (this.astStack[this.astPtr + 1] instanceof ExplicitConstructorCall) {
2627                        //avoid a isSomeThing that would only be used here BUT what is faster between two alternatives ?
2628                        System.arraycopy(
2629                                this.astStack,
2630                                this.astPtr + 2,
2631                                statements = new Statement[length - 1],
2632                                0,
2633                                length - 1);
2634                        constructorCall = (ExplicitConstructorCall) this.astStack[this.astPtr + 1];
2635                } else { //need to add explicitly the super();
2636                        System.arraycopy(
2637                                this.astStack,
2638                                this.astPtr + 1,
2639                                statements = new Statement[length],
2640                                0,
2641                                length);
2642                        constructorCall = SuperReference.implicitSuperConstructorCall();
2643                }
2644        } else {
2645                boolean insideFieldInitializer = false;
2646                if (this.diet) {
2647                        for (int i = this.nestedType; i > 0; i--){
2648                                if (this.variablesCounter[i] > 0) {
2649                                        insideFieldInitializer = true;
2650                                        break;
2651                                }
2652                        }
2653                }
2654 
2655                if (!this.diet || insideFieldInitializer){
2656                        // add it only in non-diet mode, if diet_bodies, then constructor call will be added elsewhere.
2657                        constructorCall = SuperReference.implicitSuperConstructorCall();
2658                }
2659        }
2660 
2661        // now we know that the top of stack is a constructorDeclaration
2662        ConstructorDeclaration cd = (ConstructorDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2663        cd.constructorCall = constructorCall;
2664        cd.statements = statements;
2665 
2666        //highlight of the implicit call on the method name
2667        if (constructorCall != null && cd.constructorCall.sourceEnd == 0) {
2668                cd.constructorCall.sourceEnd = cd.sourceEnd;
2669                cd.constructorCall.sourceStart = cd.sourceStart;
2670        }
2671 
2672        if (!(this.diet && this.dietInt == 0)
2673                        && statements == null
2674                        && (constructorCall == null || constructorCall.isImplicitSuper())
2675                        && !containsComment(cd.bodyStart, this.endPosition)) {
2676                        cd.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
2677 
2678        }
2679 
2680        //watch for } that could be given as a unicode ! ( u007D is '}' )
2681        // store the this.endPosition (position just before the '}') in case there is
2682        // a trailing comment behind the end of the method
2683        cd.bodyEnd = this.endPosition;
2684        cd.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
2685}
2686protected void consumeConstructorHeader() {
2687        // ConstructorHeader ::= ConstructorHeaderName MethodHeaderParameters MethodHeaderThrowsClauseopt
2688 
2689        AbstractMethodDeclaration method = (AbstractMethodDeclaration)this.astStack[this.astPtr];
2690 
2691        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameLBRACE){
2692                method.bodyStart = this.scanner.currentPosition;
2693        }
2694        // recovery
2695        if (this.currentElement != null){
2696                if (this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON){ // for invalid constructors
2697                        method.modifiers |= ExtraCompilerModifiers.AccSemicolonBody;
2698                        method.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition-1;
2699                        method.bodyEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition-1;
2700                        if (this.currentElement.parseTree() == method && this.currentElement.parent != null) {
2701                                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.parent;
2702                        }
2703                }
2704                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
2705        }
2706}
2707protected void consumeConstructorHeaderName() {
2708 
2709        /* recovering - might be an empty message send */
2710        if (this.currentElement != null){
2711                if (this.lastIgnoredToken == TokenNamenew){ // was an allocation expression
2712                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.startPosition; // force to restart at this exact position
2713                        this.restartRecovery = true;
2714                        return;
2715                }
2716        }
2717 
2718        // ConstructorHeaderName ::=  Modifiersopt 'Identifier' '('
2719        ConstructorDeclaration cd = new ConstructorDeclaration(this.compilationUnit.compilationResult);
2720 
2721        //name -- this is not really revelant but we do .....
2722        cd.selector = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr];
2723        long selectorSource = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--];
2724        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
2725 
2726        //modifiers
2727        cd.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2728        cd.modifiers = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
2729        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
2730        
2731        // javadoc
2732        cd.javadoc = this.javadoc;
2733        this.javadoc = null;
2734 
2735        //highlight starts at the selector starts
2736        cd.sourceStart = (int) (selectorSource >>> 32);
2737        pushOnAstStack(cd);
2738        cd.sourceEnd = this.lParenPos;
2739        cd.bodyStart = this.lParenPos+1;
2740        this.listLength = 0; // initialize this.listLength before reading parameters/throws
2741 
2742        // recovery
2743        if (this.currentElement != null){
2744                this.lastCheckPoint = cd.bodyStart;
2745                if ((this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredType && this.lastIgnoredToken != TokenNameDOT)
2746                        || cd.modifiers != 0){
2747                        this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(cd, 0);
2748                        this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
2749                }
2750        }
2751}

2756                if (this.lastIgnoredToken == TokenNamenew){ // was an allocation expression

2780

2796                        || cd.modifiers != 0){
2797                        this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(cd, 0);
2798                        this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
2799                }
2800        }

2927protected void consumeEmptyStatement() {
2928        // EmptyStatement ::= ';'
2929        char[] source = this.scanner.source;
2930        if (source[this.endStatementPosition] == ';') {
2931                pushOnAstStack(new EmptyStatement(this.endStatementPosition, this.endStatementPosition));
2932        } else {
2933                if(source.length > 5) {
2934                        int c1 = 0, c2 = 0, c3 = 0, c4 = 0;
2935                        int pos = this.endStatementPosition - 4;
2936                        while (source[pos] == 'u') {
2937                                pos--;
2938                        }
2939                        if (source[pos] == '\\' &&
2940                                        !((c1 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(source[this.endStatementPosition - 3])) > 15
2941                                                || c1 < 0
2942                                                || (c2 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(source[this.endStatementPosition - 2])) > 15
2943                                                || c2 < 0
2944                                                || (c3 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(source[this.endStatementPosition - 1])) > 15
2945                                                || c3 < 0
2946                                                || (c4 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(source[this.endStatementPosition])) > 15
2947                                                || c4 < 0) &&
2948                                        ((char) (((c1 * 16 + c2) * 16 + c3) * 16 + c4)) == ';'){
2949                                // we have a Unicode for the ';' (/u003B)
2950                                pushOnAstStack(new EmptyStatement(pos, this.endStatementPosition));
2951                                return;
2952                        }
2953                }
2954                pushOnAstStack(new EmptyStatement(this.endStatementPosition, this.endStatementPosition));
2955        }
2956}

3252protected void consumeEnumConstantHeader() {

3274         this.expressionPtr -= length;
3275         System.arraycopy(
3276               this.expressionStack,
3277               this.expressionPtr + 1,
3278               allocationExpression.arguments = new Expression[length],
3279               0,
3280               length);
3281      }
3282      enumConstant.initialization = allocationExpression;
3283   } else {
3284      AllocationExpression allocationExpression = new AllocationExpression();
3285      allocationExpression.enumConstant = enumConstant;
3286      // fill arguments if needed
3287      int length;
3288      if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
3289         this.expressionPtr -= length;
3290         System.arraycopy(
3291               this.expressionStack,
3292               this.expressionPtr + 1,
3293               allocationExpression.arguments = new Expression[length],
3294               0,
3295               length);
3296      }
3297      enumConstant.initialization = allocationExpression;
3298   }
3299 
3300   // recovery
3301   if (this.currentElement != null) {
3302          if(foundOpeningBrace) {
3303                  TypeDeclaration anonymousType = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
3304                  this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(anonymousType, 0);
3305              this.lastCheckPoint = anonymousType.bodyStart;
3306        this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
3307        this.currentToken = 0; // opening brace already taken into account
3308          } else {
3309                    if(this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON) {
3310                          RecoveredType currentType = this.currentRecoveryType();
3311                        if(currentType != null) {
3312                                currentType.insideEnumConstantPart = false;
3313                        }
3314                  }
3315                  this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.startPosition; // force to restart at this exact position
3316              this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
3317              this.restartRecovery = true;
3318          }
3319   }

3342protected void consumeEnumDeclaration() {
3343        // EnumDeclaration ::= EnumHeader ClassHeaderImplementsopt EnumBody
3344        int length;
3345        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
3346                //there are length declarations
3347                //dispatch according to the type of the declarations
3348                dispatchDeclarationIntoEnumDeclaration(length);

3350

3352

3354        markInitializersWithLocalType(enumDeclaration);
3355 
3356        //convert constructor that do not have the type's name into methods
3357        boolean hasConstructor = enumDeclaration.checkConstructors(this);
3358 
3359        //add the default constructor when needed
3360        if (!hasConstructor) {

3365                                        insideFieldInitializer = true;

3367                                }

3369                }

3371        }

3375                enumDeclaration.bits |= ASTNode.ContainsAssertion;
3376        }

3378        enumDeclaration.bodyEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
3379        if (length == 0 && !containsComment(enumDeclaration.bodyStart, enumDeclaration.bodyEnd)) {
3380                enumDeclaration.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
3381        }

3401protected void consumeEnumHeaderName() {

3404        if (this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType] == 0) {

3406                        enumDeclaration.bits |= ASTNode.IsMemberType;

3517protected void consumeExplicitConstructorInvocation(int flag, int recFlag) {
3518 
3519        /* flag allows to distinguish 3 cases :
3520        (0) :
3521        ExplicitConstructorInvocation ::= 'this' '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ';'
3522        ExplicitConstructorInvocation ::= 'super' '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ';'
3523        (1) :
3524        ExplicitConstructorInvocation ::= Primary '.' 'super' '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ';'
3525        ExplicitConstructorInvocation ::= Primary '.' 'this' '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ';'
3526        (2) :
3527        ExplicitConstructorInvocation ::= Name '.' 'super' '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ';'
3528        ExplicitConstructorInvocation ::= Name '.' 'this' '(' ArgumentListopt ')' ';'
3529        */
3530        int startPosition = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
3531        ExplicitConstructorCall ecc = new ExplicitConstructorCall(recFlag);
3532        int length;
3533        if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
3534                this.expressionPtr -= length;
3535                System.arraycopy(this.expressionStack, this.expressionPtr + 1, ecc.arguments = new Expression[length], 0, length);
3536        }
3537        switch (flag) {
3538                case 0 :
3539                        ecc.sourceStart = startPosition;
3540                        break;
3541                case 1 :
3542                        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
3543                        ecc.sourceStart = (ecc.qualification = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--]).sourceStart;
3544                        break;
3545                case 2 :
3546                        ecc.sourceStart = (ecc.qualification = getUnspecifiedReferenceOptimized()).sourceStart;
3547                        break;
3548        }
3549        pushOnAstStack(ecc);
3550        ecc.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
3551}

3600protected void consumeFieldAccess(boolean isSuperAccess) {
3601        // FieldAccess ::= Primary '.' 'Identifier'
3602        // FieldAccess ::= 'super' '.' 'Identifier'
3603 
3604        FieldReference fr =
3605                new FieldReference(
3606                        this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
3607                        this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
3608        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
3609        if (isSuperAccess) {
3610                //considerates the fieldReference beginning at the 'super' ....
3611                fr.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
3612                fr.receiver = new SuperReference(fr.sourceStart, this.endPosition);
3613                pushOnExpressionStack(fr);
3614        } else {
3615                //optimize push/pop
3616                fr.receiver = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
3617                //fieldreference begins at the receiver
3618                fr.sourceStart = fr.receiver.sourceStart;
3619                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = fr;
3620        }
3621}
3622protected void consumeFieldDeclaration() {
3623        // See consumeLocalVariableDeclarationDefaultModifier() in case of change: duplicated code
3624        // FieldDeclaration ::= Modifiersopt Type VariableDeclarators ';'
3625 
3626        /*
3627        this.astStack :
3628        this.expressionStack: Expression Expression ...... Expression
3629        this.identifierStack : type  identifier identifier ...... identifier
3630        this.intStack : typeDim      dim        dim               dim
3631         ==>
3632        this.astStack : FieldDeclaration FieldDeclaration ...... FieldDeclaration
3633        this.expressionStack :
3634        this.identifierStack :
3635        this.intStack :
3636 
3637        */
3638        int variableDeclaratorsCounter = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr];
3639 
3640        for (int i = variableDeclaratorsCounter - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3641                FieldDeclaration fieldDeclaration = (FieldDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr - i];
3642                fieldDeclaration.declarationSourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
3643                fieldDeclaration.declarationEnd = this.endStatementPosition;        // semi-colon included
3644        }
3645 
3646        updateSourceDeclarationParts(variableDeclaratorsCounter);
3647        int endPos = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
3648        if (endPos != this.endStatementPosition) {
3649                for (int i = 0; i < variableDeclaratorsCounter; i++) {
3650                        FieldDeclaration fieldDeclaration = (FieldDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr - i];
3651                        fieldDeclaration.declarationSourceEnd = endPos;
3652                }
3653        }
3654        // update the this.astStack, this.astPtr and this.astLengthStack
3655        int startIndex = this.astPtr - this.variablesCounter[this.nestedType] + 1;
3656        System.arraycopy(
3657                this.astStack,
3658                startIndex,
3659                this.astStack,
3660                startIndex - 1,
3661                variableDeclaratorsCounter);
3662        this.astPtr--; // remove the type reference
3663        this.astLengthStack[--this.astLengthPtr] = variableDeclaratorsCounter;
3664 
3665        // recovery
3666        if (this.currentElement != null) {
3667                this.lastCheckPoint = endPos + 1;
3668                if (this.currentElement.parent != null && this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredField){
3669                        if (!(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredInitializer)) {
3670                                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.parent;
3671                        }
3672                }
3673                this.restartRecovery = true;
3674        }
3675        this.variablesCounter[this.nestedType] = 0;
3676}

3718        int modifierPositions=(int) (namePositions >>> 32);
3719        Argument arg =
3720                new Argument(
3721                        identifierName,
3722                        namePositions,
3723                        null,
3724                         ClassFileConstants.AccDefault);
3725//        this.intStack[this.intPtr + 1] & ~ClassFileConstants.AccDeprecated); // modifiers
3726        arg.declarationSourceStart = modifierPositions;
3727        // consume annotations
3728//        int length;
3729//        if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
3730//                System.arraycopy(
3731//                        this.expressionStack,
3732//                        (this.expressionPtr -= length) + 1,
3733//                        arg.annotations = new Annotation[length],
3734//                        0,
3735//                        length);
3736//        }
3737        if (this.options.inferOptions.saveArgumentComments)
3738        {
3739                handleArgumentComment(arg);
3740        }
3741        
3742        
3743        pushOnAstStack(arg);
3744 
3745        /* if incomplete method header, this.listLength counter will not have been reset,
3746                indicating that some arguments are available on the stack */
3747        this.listLength++;
3748}

3750protected void handleArgumentComment(Argument arg)
3751{
3752        int lastComment = this.scanner.commentPtr;
3753 
3754//        if (this.modifiersSourceStart >= 0) {
3755//                // eliminate comments located after modifierSourceStart if positionned
3756//                while (lastComment >= 0 && this.scanner.commentStarts[lastComment] > this.modifiersSourceStart) lastComment--;
3757//        }
3758        if (lastComment >= 0 && this.scanner.commentStops[0]<0) {
3759                // consider all remaining leading comments to be part of current declaration
3760                int start=this.scanner.commentStarts[0];
3761                int end=this.scanner.commentStops[0];
3762                arg.comment=CharOperation.subarray(this.scanner.source, start+2, (-end)-2);
3763                this.scanner.commentPtr=-1;
3764        }
3765}

3792                this.flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(impt.declarationSourceEnd);

3796                this.lastCheckPoint = impt.declarationSourceEnd + 1;
3797                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(impt, 0);
3798                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
3799                this.restartRecovery = true;
3800                // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
3801        }

3851protected void consumeInterfaceDeclaration() {
3852        // see consumeClassDeclaration in case of changes: duplicated code
3853        // InterfaceDeclaration ::= InterfaceHeader InterfaceBody
3854        int length;
3855        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
3856                //there are length declarations
3857                //dispatch.....according to the type of the declarations
3858                dispatchDeclarationInto(length);
3859        }
3860 
3861        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
3862 
3863        // mark initializers with local type mark if needed
3864        markInitializersWithLocalType(typeDecl);
3865 
3866        //convert constructor that do not have the type's name into methods
3867        typeDecl.checkConstructors(this);
3868 
3869        //always add <clinit> (will be remove at code gen time if empty)
3870        if (this.scanner.containsAssertKeyword) {
3871                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.ContainsAssertion;
3872        }
3873        typeDecl.addClinit();
3874        typeDecl.bodyEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
3875        if (length == 0 && !containsComment(typeDecl.bodyStart, typeDecl.bodyEnd)) {
3876                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
3877        }
3878        typeDecl.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
3879}
3880protected void consumeInterfaceHeader() {

3882

3884        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameLBRACE){
3885                typeDecl.bodyStart = this.scanner.currentPosition;
3886        }
3887        if (this.currentElement != null){
3888                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
3889        }
3890        // flush the comments related to the interface header
3891        this.scanner.commentPtr = -1;

3893protected void consumeInterfaceHeaderExtends() {
3894        // InterfaceHeaderExtends ::= 'extends' InterfaceTypeList
3895        int length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--];
3896        //super interfaces
3897        this.astPtr -= length;
3898        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
3899        System.arraycopy(
3900                this.astStack,
3901                this.astPtr + 1,
3902                typeDecl.superInterfaces = new TypeReference[length],
3903                0,
3904                length);
3905        for (int i = 0, max = typeDecl.superInterfaces.length; i < max; i++) {
3906                typeDecl.superInterfaces[i].bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
3907        }
3908        typeDecl.bodyStart = typeDecl.superInterfaces[length-1].sourceEnd + 1;
3909        this.listLength = 0; // reset after having read super-interfaces
3910        // recovery
3911        if (this.currentElement != null) {
3912                this.lastCheckPoint = typeDecl.bodyStart;
3913        }

3915protected void consumeInterfaceHeaderName1() {
3916        // InterfaceHeaderName ::= Modifiersopt 'interface' 'Identifier'
3917        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = new TypeDeclaration(this.compilationUnit.compilationResult);
3918 
3919        if (this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType] == 0) {
3920                if (this.nestedType != 0) {
3921                        typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.IsMemberType;
3922                }
3923        } else {
3924                // Record that the block has a declaration for local types
3925                typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.IsLocalType;
3926                markEnclosingMemberWithLocalType();
3927                blockReal();
3928        }
3929 
3930        //highlight the name of the type
3931        long pos = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr];
3932        typeDecl.sourceEnd = (int) pos;
3933        typeDecl.sourceStart = (int) (pos >>> 32);
3934        typeDecl.name = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr--];
3935        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
3936 
3937        //compute the declaration source too
3938        // 'class' and 'interface' push two int positions: the beginning of the class token and its end.
3939        // we want to keep the beginning position but get rid of the end position
3940        // it is only used for the ClassLiteralAccess positions.
3941        typeDecl.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
3942        this.intPtr--; // remove the end position of the class token
3943        typeDecl.modifiersSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
3944        typeDecl.modifiers = this.intStack[this.intPtr--] | ClassFileConstants.AccInterface;
3945        if (typeDecl.modifiersSourceStart >= 0) {
3946                typeDecl.declarationSourceStart = typeDecl.modifiersSourceStart;
3947        }
3948 
3949        // Store secondary info
3950        if ((typeDecl.bits & ASTNode.IsMemberType) == 0 && (typeDecl.bits & ASTNode.IsLocalType) == 0) {
3951                if (this.compilationUnit != null && !CharOperation.equals(typeDecl.name, this.compilationUnit.getMainTypeName())) {
3952                        typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.IsSecondaryType;
3953                }
3954        }
3955        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
3956        
3957        typeDecl.bodyStart = typeDecl.sourceEnd + 1;
3958        pushOnAstStack(typeDecl);
3959        this.listLength = 0; // will be updated when reading super-interfaces
3960        // recovery
3961        if (this.currentElement != null){ // is recovering
3962                this.lastCheckPoint = typeDecl.bodyStart;
3963                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(typeDecl, 0);
3964                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
3965        }
3966        // javadoc
3967        typeDecl.javadoc = this.javadoc;
3968        this.javadoc = null;
3969}

4022protected void consumeInvalidConstructorDeclaration(boolean hasBody) {
4023        // InvalidConstructorDeclaration ::= ConstructorHeader ConstructorBody ==> true
4024        // InvalidConstructorDeclaration ::= ConstructorHeader ';' ==> false
4025 
4026        /*
4027        this.astStack : modifiers arguments throws statements
4028        this.identifierStack : name
4029         ==>
4030        this.astStack : FunctionDeclaration
4031        this.identifierStack :
4032        */
4033        if (hasBody) {
4034                // pop the position of the {  (body of the method) pushed in block decl
4035                this.intPtr--;
4036        }
4037 
4038        //statements
4039        if (hasBody) {
4040                this.realBlockPtr--;
4041        }
4042 
4043        int length;
4044        if (hasBody && ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0)) {
4045                this.astPtr -= length;
4046        }
4047        ConstructorDeclaration constructorDeclaration = (ConstructorDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
4048        constructorDeclaration.bodyEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
4049        constructorDeclaration.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
4050        if (!hasBody) {
4051                constructorDeclaration.modifiers |= ExtraCompilerModifiers.AccSemicolonBody;
4052        }

4141protected void consumeLocalVariableDeclarationStatement() {
4142        // LocalVariableDeclarationStatement ::= LocalVariableDeclaration ';'
4143        // see blockReal in case of change: duplicated code
4144        // increment the amount of declared variables for this block
4145        this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr]++;
4146 
4147        // update source end to include the semi-colon
4148        int variableDeclaratorsCounter = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr];
4149        AbstractVariableDeclaration nextDeclaration =null;
4150        for (int i = 0; i<variableDeclaratorsCounter; i++) {
4151                AbstractVariableDeclaration localDeclaration = (AbstractVariableDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr - i];
4152                localDeclaration.declarationSourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
4153                localDeclaration.declarationEnd = this.endStatementPosition;        // semi-colon included
4154                localDeclaration.nextLocal=nextDeclaration;
4155                nextDeclaration=localDeclaration;
4156        }
4157        this.astPtr-=variableDeclaratorsCounter-1;
4158        this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr]=1;
4159        this.lastCheckPoint = endStatementPosition+1;
4160

4194protected void consumeMethodDeclaration(boolean isNotAbstract) {
4195        // FunctionDeclaration ::= MethodHeader MethodBody
4196        // AbstractMethodDeclaration ::= MethodHeader ';'
4197 
4198        /*
4199        this.astStack : modifiers arguments throws statements
4200        this.identifierStack : type name
4201        this.intStack : dim dim dim
4202         ==>
4203        this.astStack : FunctionDeclaration
4204        this.identifierStack :
4205        this.intStack :
4206        */
4207 
4208 
4209        this.nestedType--;
4210        int length;
4211        if (isNotAbstract) {
4212                // pop the position of the {  (body of the method) pushed in block decl
4213                this.intPtr--;
4214                this.intPtr--;
4215        }
4216 
4217        int explicitDeclarations = 0;
4218        Statement[] statements = null;
4219        if (isNotAbstract) {
4220                //statements
4221                explicitDeclarations = this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr--];
4222                if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
4223                        System.arraycopy(
4224                                this.astStack,
4225                                (this.astPtr -= length) + 1,
4226                                statements = new Statement[length],
4227                                0,
4228                                length);
4229                }
4230        }
4231 
4232        // now we know that we have a method declaration at the top of the ast stack
4233        MethodDeclaration md = (MethodDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
4234        md.statements = statements;
4235        md.explicitDeclarations = explicitDeclarations;
4236 
4237        // cannot be done in consumeMethodHeader because we have no idea whether or not there
4238        // is a body when we reduce the method header
4239        if (!isNotAbstract) { //remember the fact that the method has a semicolon body
4240                md.modifiers |= ExtraCompilerModifiers.AccSemicolonBody;
4241        } else if (!(this.diet && this.dietInt == 0) && statements == null && !containsComment(md.bodyStart, this.endPosition)) {
4242                md.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
4243        }
4244        // store the this.endPosition (position just before the '}') in case there is
4245        // a trailing comment behind the end of the method
4246        md.bodyEnd = this.endPosition;
4247        md.sourceEnd = this.endPosition;
4248        md.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
4249}
4250protected void consumeMethodHeader() {
4251        // MethodHeader ::= MethodHeaderName MethodHeaderParameters MethodHeaderExtendedDims ThrowsClauseopt
4252        // AnnotationMethodHeader ::= AnnotationMethodHeaderName FormalParameterListopt MethodHeaderRightParen MethodHeaderExtendedDims AnnotationMethodHeaderDefaultValueopt
4253        // RecoveryMethodHeader ::= RecoveryMethodHeaderName FormalParameterListopt MethodHeaderRightParen MethodHeaderExtendedDims AnnotationMethodHeaderDefaultValueopt
4254        // RecoveryMethodHeader ::= RecoveryMethodHeaderName FormalParameterListopt MethodHeaderRightParen MethodHeaderExtendedDims MethodHeaderThrowsClause
4255 
4256        // retrieve end position of method declarator
4257        AbstractMethodDeclaration method = (AbstractMethodDeclaration)this.astStack[this.astPtr];
4258 
4259        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameLBRACE){
4260                method.bodyStart = this.scanner.currentPosition;
4261        }
4262         else if (currentToken != TokenNameSEMICOLON) { // insert semicolon
4263                        currentToken = TokenNameSEMICOLON;
4264                        scanner.pushBack();
4265                }
4266        // recovery
4267        if (this.currentElement != null){
4268//                if(method.isAnnotationMethod()) {
4269//                        method.modifiers |= AccSemicolonBody;
4270//                        method.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition-1;
4271//                        method.bodyEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition-1;
4272//                        this.currentElement = this.currentElement.parent;
4273//                } else
4274                if (this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON /*&& !method.isAnnotationMethod()*/){
4275                        method.modifiers |= ExtraCompilerModifiers.AccSemicolonBody;
4276                        method.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition-1;
4277                        method.bodyEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition-1;
4278//                        if (this.currentElement.parseTree() == method && this.currentElement.parent != null) {
4279//                                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.parent;
4280//                        }
4281                } else if(this.currentToken == TokenNameLBRACE) {
4282                        if (this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredMethod &&
4283                                        ((RecoveredMethod)this.currentElement).methodDeclaration != method) {
4284                                this.ignoreNextOpeningBrace = true;
4285                                this.currentElement.bracketBalance++;
4286                }                        }
4287                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
4288        }
4289}

4548protected void consumeMethodInvocationPrimary() {
4549        //optimize the push/pop
4550        //FunctionInvocation ::= Primary '.' 'Identifier' '(' ArgumentListopt ')'
4551 
4552        MessageSend m = newMessageSend();
4553//        m.sourceStart =
4554//                (int) ((m.nameSourcePosition = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr]) >>> 32);

4558        Expression receiver = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
4559        m.sourceStart = receiver.sourceStart;

4561        {

4563                m.selector=singleNameReference.token;
4564                 m.nameSourcePosition = (((long) singleNameReference.sourceStart) << 32)+(singleNameReference.sourceStart+m.selector.length-1);
4565                 receiver=null;

4568                FieldReference fieldReference = (FieldReference) receiver;
4569                m.selector=fieldReference.token;

4571                receiver=fieldReference.receiver;
4572        }
4573 
4574 
4575        m.receiver = receiver;
4576        m.sourceEnd = this.rParenPos;
4577        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = m;

4606        m.nameSourcePosition = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr];
4607        m.selector = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr--];
4608        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
4609        m.receiver = new SuperReference(m.sourceStart, this.endPosition);
4610        pushOnExpressionStack(m);
4611}

4616        intPtr--; // start position of the typeArguments

4659protected void incrementNestedType() {
4660        int length = this.nestedMethod.length;
4661        if (++this.nestedType >= length) {
4662                System.arraycopy(
4663                        this.nestedMethod, 0,
4664                        this.nestedMethod = new int[length + 30], 0,
4665                        length);
4666                // increase the size of the variablesCounter as well. It has to be consistent with the size of the nestedMethod collection
4667                System.arraycopy(
4668                        this.variablesCounter, 0,
4669                        this.variablesCounter = new int[length + 30], 0,
4670                        length);
4671        }
4672        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType] = 0;
4673        this.variablesCounter[this.nestedType] = 0;
4674}

4702protected void consumePackageDeclaration() {
4703        // PackageDeclaration ::= 'package' Name ';'
4704        /* build an ImportRef build from the last name
4705        stored in the identifier stack. */
4706 
4707        ImportReference impt = this.compilationUnit.currentPackage;
4708        this.compilationUnit.javadoc = this.javadoc;
4709        this.javadoc = null;
4710        // flush comments defined prior to import statements
4711        impt.declarationEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
4712        impt.declarationSourceEnd = this.flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(impt.declarationSourceEnd);

4714protected void consumePackageDeclarationName() {
4715        // PackageDeclarationName ::= 'package' Name
4716        /* build an ImportRef build from the last name
4717        stored in the identifier stack. */
4718 
4719        ImportReference impt;
4720        int length;
4721        char[][] tokens =
4722                new char[length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--]][];
4723        this.identifierPtr -= length;
4724        long[] positions = new long[length];
4725        System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, ++this.identifierPtr, tokens, 0, length);
4726        System.arraycopy(
4727                this.identifierPositionStack,
4728                this.identifierPtr--,
4729                positions,
4730                0,
4731                length);
4732 
4733        impt = new ImportReference(tokens, positions, true);
4734        this.compilationUnit.currentPackage = impt;
4735 
4736        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON){
4737                impt.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition - 1;
4738        } else {
4739                impt.declarationSourceEnd = impt.sourceEnd;
4740        }
4741        impt.declarationEnd = impt.declarationSourceEnd;
4742        //this.endPosition is just before the ;
4743        impt.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
4744 
4745        // get possible comment source start
4746        if(this.javadoc != null) {
4747                impt.declarationSourceStart = this.javadoc.sourceStart;
4748        }
4749 
4750        // recovery
4751        if (this.currentElement != null){
4752                this.lastCheckPoint = impt.declarationSourceEnd+1;
4753                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
4754        }
4755}
4756protected void consumePackageDeclarationNameWithModifiers() {
4757        // PackageDeclarationName ::= Modifiers 'package' Name
4758        /* build an ImportRef build from the last name
4759        stored in the identifier stack. */
4760 
4761        ImportReference impt;
4762        int length;
4763        char[][] tokens =
4764                new char[length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--]][];
4765        this.identifierPtr -= length;
4766        long[] positions = new long[length];

4768        System.arraycopy(
4769                this.identifierPositionStack,
4770                this.identifierPtr--,
4771                positions,
4772                0,
4773                length);

4785                // get possible comment source start

4788                }
4789        }
4790 
4791        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON){
4792                impt.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition - 1;
4793        } else {
4794                impt.declarationSourceEnd = impt.sourceEnd;
4795        }
4796        impt.declarationEnd = impt.declarationSourceEnd;
4797 
4798        // recovery
4799        if (this.currentElement != null){
4800                this.lastCheckPoint = impt.declarationSourceEnd+1;
4801                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
4802        }

4814protected void consumePrimaryNoNewArray() {

4816        final Expression parenthesizedExpression = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];

4819        parenthesizedExpression.bits &= ~ASTNode.ParenthesizedMASK;
4820        parenthesizedExpression.bits |= (numberOfParenthesis + 1) << ASTNode.ParenthesizedSHIFT;

6071        {
6072                pushOnExpressionStack(new EmptyExpression(this.endPosition,this.endPosition));
6073        }
6074        concatExpressionLists();
6075//    this.intStack[this.intPtr]&= ~(UNCONSUMED_ELISION|UNCONSUMED_LIT_ELEMENT);
6076}

6080                   concatExpressionLists();
6081        this.intStack[this.intPtr]|=(WAS_ARRAY_LIT_ELEMENT|UNCONSUMED_ELISION) ;
6082

6119                pushOnExpressionStack(new EmptyExpression(this.endPosition,this.endPosition));
6120                concatExpressionLists();
6121        }

6130private void consumeLiteralField() {
6131        // MemberValuePair ::= SimpleName '=' MemberValue
6132        this.modifiersSourceStart=-1;
6133        this.checkComment();
6134        this.resetModifiers();
6135 
6136        Expression value = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--];
6137        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
6138 
6139        Expression field = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--];
6140        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
6141        int end = value.sourceEnd;
6142        int start = field.sourceStart;
6143 
6144        ObjectLiteralField literalField = new ObjectLiteralField(field, value, start, end);
6145        pushOnExpressionStack(literalField);
6146 
6147        if (this.javadoc!=null)
6148                literalField.javaDoc = this.javadoc;
6149        else if (value instanceof FunctionExpression)
6150        {
6151                MethodDeclaration methodDeclaration = ((FunctionExpression)value).methodDeclaration;
6152                literalField.javaDoc=methodDeclaration.javadoc;
6153                methodDeclaration.javadoc=null;
6154        }
6155        this.javadoc = null;
6156 
6157        // discard obsolete comments while inside methods or fields initializer (see bug 74369)
6158        if (!(this.diet && this.dietInt==0) && this.scanner.commentPtr >= 0) {
6159                flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(literalField.sourceEnd);
6160        }
6161        resetModifiers();
6162}

6172private void consumeObjectLiteral() {
6173        ObjectLiteral objectLiteral = new ObjectLiteral();
6174        int length;
6175        if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
6176                this.expressionPtr -= length;
6177                System.arraycopy(
6178                        this.expressionStack,
6179                        this.expressionPtr + 1,
6180                        objectLiteral.fields = new ObjectLiteralField[length],
6181                        0,
6182                        length);
6183        }
6184        objectLiteral.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
6185        objectLiteral.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6186 
6187        pushOnExpressionStack(objectLiteral);

6198        protected void consumePropertyOperator() {

6201                new FieldReference(
6202                        this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
6203                        this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
6204        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
6205                //optimize push/pop
6206        fr.receiver = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
6207        //fieldreference begins at the receiver

6216protected void consumeSingleTypeImportDeclarationName() {
6217        // SingleTypeImportDeclarationName ::= 'import' Name
6218        /* push an ImportRef build from the last name
6219        stored in the identifier stack. */
6220 
6221        ImportReference impt;
6222        int length;
6223        char[][] tokens = new char[length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--]][];
6224        this.identifierPtr -= length;
6225        long[] positions = new long[length];
6226        System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, length);
6227        System.arraycopy(this.identifierPositionStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, positions, 0, length);
6228        pushOnAstStack(impt = new ImportReference(tokens, positions, false));
6229 
6230        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON){
6231                impt.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition - 1;
6232        } else {
6233                impt.declarationSourceEnd = impt.sourceEnd;
6234        }
6235        impt.declarationEnd = impt.declarationSourceEnd;
6236        //this.endPosition is just before the ;
6237        impt.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6238 
6239        // recovery
6240        if (this.currentElement != null){
6241                this.lastCheckPoint = impt.declarationSourceEnd+1;
6242                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(impt, 0);
6243                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
6244                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
6245        }
6246}
6247protected void consumeStatementBreak() {
6248        // BreakStatement ::= 'break' ';'
6249        // break pushs a position on this.intStack in case there is no label
6250 
6251        pushOnAstStack(new BreakStatement(null, this.intStack[this.intPtr--], this.endStatementPosition));
6252        if (this.pendingRecoveredType != null) {
6253                // Used only in statements recovery.
6254                // This is not a real break statement but a placeholder for an existing local type.
6255                // The break statement must be replace by the local type.
6256                if (this.pendingRecoveredType.allocation == null &&
6257                                this.endPosition <= this.pendingRecoveredType.declarationSourceEnd) {
6258                        this.astStack[this.astPtr] = this.pendingRecoveredType;
6259                        this.pendingRecoveredType = null;
6260                        return;
6261                }
6262                this.pendingRecoveredType = null;
6263        }
6264}

6276protected void consumeStatementCatch() {

6278 
6279        //catch are stored directly into the Try
6280        //has they always comes two by two....
6281        //we remove one entry from the astlengthPtr.
6282        //The construction of the try statement must
6283        //then fetch the catches using  2*i and 2*i + 1
6284 
6285        this.astLengthPtr--;
6286        this.listLength = 0; // reset formalParameter counter (incremented for catch variable)
6287}

6309protected void consumeStatementDo() {
6310        // DoStatement ::= 'do' Statement 'while' '(' Expression ')' ';'
6311 
6312        //the 'while' pushes a value on this.intStack that we need to remove
6313        this.intPtr--;
6314 
6315        Statement statement = (Statement) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
6316        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
6317        this.astStack[this.astPtr] =
6318                new DoStatement(
6319                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--],
6320                        statement,
6321                        this.intStack[this.intPtr--],
6322                        this.endStatementPosition);
6323}
6324protected void consumeStatementExpressionList() {
6325        // StatementExpressionList ::= StatementExpressionList ',' StatementExpression
6326        concatExpressionLists();
6327}
6328protected void consumeStatementFor() {
6329        // ForStatement ::= 'for' '(' ForInitopt ';' Expressionopt ';' ForUpdateopt ')' Statement
6330        // ForStatementNoShortIf ::= 'for' '(' ForInitopt ';' Expressionopt ';' ForUpdateopt ')' StatementNoShortIf
6331 
6332        int length;
6333        Expression cond = null;
6334        Statement[] inits, updates;
6335        boolean scope = true;
6336 
6337        //statements
6338        this.astLengthPtr--;
6339        Statement statement = (Statement) this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
6340 
6341        //updates are on the expresion stack
6342        if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) == 0) {
6343                updates = null;
6344        } else {
6345                this.expressionPtr -= length;
6346                System.arraycopy(
6347                        this.expressionStack,
6348                        this.expressionPtr + 1,
6349                        updates = new Statement[length],
6350                        0,
6351                        length);
6352        }
6353 
6354        if (this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--] != 0)
6355                cond = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--];
6356 
6357        //inits may be on two different stacks
6358        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) == 0) {
6359                inits = null;
6360                scope = false;
6361        } else {
6362                if (length == -1) { //on this.expressionStack
6363                        scope = false;
6364                        length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--];
6365                        this.expressionPtr -= length;
6366                        System.arraycopy(
6367                                this.expressionStack,
6368                                this.expressionPtr + 1,
6369                                inits = new Statement[length],
6370                                0,
6371                                length);
6372                } else { //on this.astStack
6373                        this.astPtr -= length;
6374                        System.arraycopy(
6375                                this.astStack,
6376                                this.astPtr + 1,
6377                                inits = new Statement[length],
6378                                0,
6379                                length);
6380                }
6381        }
6382        pushOnAstStack(
6383                new ForStatement(
6384                        inits,
6385                        cond,
6386                        updates,
6387                        statement,
6388                        scope,
6389                        this.intStack[this.intPtr--],
6390                        this.endStatementPosition));
6391}
6392protected void consumeStatementIfNoElse() {
6393        // IfThenStatement ::=  'if' '(' Expression ')' Statement
6394 
6395        //optimize the push/pop
6396        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
6397        Statement thenStatement = (Statement) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
6398        this.astStack[this.astPtr] =
6399                new IfStatement(
6400                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--],
6401                        thenStatement,
6402                        this.intStack[this.intPtr--],
6403                        this.endStatementPosition);
6404}
6405protected void consumeStatementIfWithElse() {
6406        // IfThenElseStatement ::=  'if' '(' Expression ')' StatementNoShortIf 'else' Statement
6407        // IfThenElseStatementNoShortIf ::=  'if' '(' Expression ')' StatementNoShortIf 'else' StatementNoShortIf
6408 
6409        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
6410 
6411        // optimized {..., Then, Else } ==> {..., If }
6412        this.astLengthPtr--;
6413 
6414        //optimize the push/pop
6415        this.astStack[--this.astPtr] =
6416                new IfStatement(
6417                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--],
6418                        (Statement) this.astStack[this.astPtr],
6419                        (Statement) this.astStack[this.astPtr + 1],
6420                        this.intStack[this.intPtr--],
6421                        this.endStatementPosition);
6422}
6423protected void consumeStatementLabel() {

6437protected void consumeStatementReturn() {

6439        // return pushs a position on this.intStack in case there is no expression
6440 
6441        if (this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--] != 0) {
6442                pushOnAstStack(
6443                        new ReturnStatement(
6444                                this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--],
6445                                this.intStack[this.intPtr--],
6446                                this.endStatementPosition)
6447                );
6448        } else {

6450        }

6452protected void consumeStatementSwitch() {
6453        // SwitchStatement ::= 'switch' OpenBlock '(' Expression ')' SwitchBlock
6454 
6455        //OpenBlock just makes the semantic action blockStart()
6456        //the block is inlined but a scope need to be created
6457        //if some declaration occurs.
6458 
6459        int length;
6460        SwitchStatement switchStatement = new SwitchStatement();
6461        this.expressionLengthPtr--;
6462        switchStatement.expression = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--];
6463        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
6464                this.astPtr -= length;
6465                System.arraycopy(
6466                        this.astStack,
6467                        this.astPtr + 1,
6468                        switchStatement.statements = new Statement[length],
6469                        0,
6470                        length);
6471        }
6472        switchStatement.explicitDeclarations = this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr--];
6473        pushOnAstStack(switchStatement);
6474        switchStatement.blockStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6475        switchStatement.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6476        switchStatement.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
6477        if (length == 0 && !containsComment(switchStatement.blockStart, switchStatement.sourceEnd)) {
6478                switchStatement.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
6479        }
6480}

6487protected void consumeStatementTry(boolean withFinally) {
6488        //TryStatement ::= 'try'  Block Catches
6489        //TryStatement ::= 'try'  Block Catchesopt Finally
6490 
6491        int length;
6492        TryStatement tryStmt = new TryStatement();
6493        //finally
6494        if (withFinally) {
6495                this.astLengthPtr--;
6496                tryStmt.finallyBlock = (Block) this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
6497        }
6498        //catches are handle by two <argument-block> [see statementCatch]
6499        if ((length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
6500                if (length == 1) {
6501                        tryStmt.catchBlocks = new Block[] {(Block) this.astStack[this.astPtr--]};
6502                        tryStmt.catchArguments = new Argument[] {(Argument) this.astStack[this.astPtr--]};
6503                } else {
6504                        Block[] bks = (tryStmt.catchBlocks = new Block[length]);
6505                        Argument[] args = (tryStmt.catchArguments = new Argument[length]);
6506                        while (length-- > 0) {
6507                                bks[length] = (Block) this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
6508                                args[length] = (Argument) this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
6509                        }
6510                }
6511        }
6512        //try
6513        this.astLengthPtr--;
6514        tryStmt.tryBlock = (Block) this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
6515 
6516        //positions
6517        tryStmt.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
6518        tryStmt.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6519        pushOnAstStack(tryStmt);
6520}

6535protected void consumeStaticInitializer() {
6536        // StaticInitializer ::=  StaticOnly Block
6537        //push an Initializer
6538        //optimize the push/pop
6539        Block block = (Block) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
6540        if (this.diet) block.bits &= ~ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock; // clear bit set since was diet
6541        Initializer initializer = new Initializer(block, ClassFileConstants.AccStatic);
6542        this.astStack[this.astPtr] = initializer;
6543        initializer.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
6544        initializer.declarationSourceEnd = flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.endStatementPosition);
6545        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType] --;
6546        initializer.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6547        initializer.bodyStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
6548        initializer.bodyEnd = this.endPosition;
6549        // doc comment
6550        initializer.javadoc = this.javadoc;
6551        this.javadoc = null;
6552 
6553        // recovery
6554        if (this.currentElement != null){
6555                this.lastCheckPoint = initializer.declarationSourceEnd;
6556                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(initializer, 0);
6557                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
6558        }
6559}
6560protected void consumeStaticOnly() {
6561        // StaticOnly ::= 'static'
6562        int savedModifiersSourceStart = this.modifiersSourceStart;
6563        checkComment(); // might update declaration source start
6564        if (this.modifiersSourceStart >= savedModifiersSourceStart) {
6565                this.modifiersSourceStart = savedModifiersSourceStart;
6566        }
6567        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition);
6568        pushOnIntStack(
6569                this.modifiersSourceStart >= 0 ? this.modifiersSourceStart : this.scanner.startPosition);
6570        jumpOverMethodBody();
6571        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]++;
6572        resetModifiers();
6573        this.expressionLengthPtr--; // remove the 0 pushed in consumeToken() for the static modifier
6574 
6575        // recovery
6576        if (this.currentElement != null){
6577                this.recoveredStaticInitializerStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr]; // remember start position only for static initializers
6578        }
6579}

6596protected void consumeToken(int type) {
6597        /* remember the last consumed value */
6598        /* try to minimize the number of build values */
6599//        // clear the commentPtr of the scanner in case we read something different from a modifier
6600//        switch(type) {
6601//                case TokenNameabstract :
6602//                case TokenNamestrictfp :
6603//                case TokenNamefinal :
6604//                case TokenNamenative :
6605//                case TokenNameprivate :
6606//                case TokenNameprotected :
6607//                case TokenNamepublic :
6608//                case TokenNametransient :
6609//                case TokenNamevolatile :
6610//                case TokenNamestatic :
6611//                case TokenNamesynchronized :
6612//                        break;
6613//                default:
6614//                        this.scanner.commentPtr = -1;
6615//        }
6616        //System.out.println(this.scanner.toStringAction(type));
6617        switch (type) {
6618                case TokenNameIdentifier :
6619                        pushIdentifier();
6620                        if (this.scanner.useAssertAsAnIndentifier  &&
6621                                        this.lastErrorEndPositionBeforeRecovery < this.scanner.currentPosition) {
6622                                long positions = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr];
6623                                if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated)
6624                                        problemReporter().useAssertAsAnIdentifier(this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],(int) (positions >>> 32), (int) positions);
6625                        }
6626                        if (this.scanner.useEnumAsAnIndentifier  &&
6627                                        this.lastErrorEndPositionBeforeRecovery < this.scanner.currentPosition) {
6628                                long positions = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr];
6629                                if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated) problemReporter().useEnumAsAnIdentifier((int) (positions >>> 32), (int) positions);
6630                        }
6631                        break;
6632                case TokenNameinterface :
6633                        //'class' is pushing two int (positions) on the stack ==> 'interface' needs to do it too....
6634                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6635                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);
6636                        break;
6637                case TokenNameabstract :
6638                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccAbstract);
6639                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6640                        break;
6641                case TokenNamestrictfp :
6642                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccStrictfp);
6643                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6644                        break;
6645                case TokenNamefinal :
6646                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccFinal);
6647                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6648                        break;
6649                case TokenNamenative :
6650                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccNative);
6651                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6652                        break;
6653                case TokenNameprivate :
6654                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccPrivate);
6655                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6656                        break;
6657                case TokenNameprotected :
6658                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccProtected);
6659                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6660                        break;
6661                case TokenNamepublic :
6662                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccPublic);
6663                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6664                        break;
6665                case TokenNametransient :
6666                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccTransient);
6667                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6668                        break;
6669                case TokenNamevolatile :
6670                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccVolatile);
6671                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6672                        break;
6673                case TokenNamestatic :
6674                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccStatic);
6675                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6676                        break;
6677//                case TokenNamesynchronized :
6678//                        this.synchronizedBlockSourceStart = this.scanner.startPosition;
6679//                        checkAndSetModifiers(ClassFileConstants.AccSynchronized);
6680//                        pushOnExpressionStackLengthStack(0);
6681//                        break;
6682                        //==============================
6683//                case TokenNamevoid :
6684//                        pushIdentifier(-T_void);
6685//                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6686//                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);
6687//                        break;
6688                        //push a default dimension while void is not part of the primitive
6689                        //declaration baseType and so takes the place of a type without getting into
6690                        //regular type parsing that generates a dimension on this.intStack
6691                case TokenNameboolean :
6692                        pushIdentifier(-T_boolean);
6693                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6694                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);
6695                        break;
6696                case TokenNamebyte :
6697                        pushIdentifier(-T_byte);
6698                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6699                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);
6700                        break;
6701                case TokenNamechar :
6702                        pushIdentifier(-T_char);
6703                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6704                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);
6705                        break;
6706                case TokenNamedouble :
6707                        pushIdentifier(-T_double);
6708                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6709                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);

6711                case TokenNamefloat :

6726                case TokenNameshort :

6728                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
6729                        pushOnIntStack(this.scanner.startPosition);
6730                        break;
6731                        //==============================
6732                case TokenNameIntegerLiteral :
6733                        pushOnExpressionStack(
6734                                new IntLiteral(
6735                                        this.scanner.getCurrentTokenSource(),

6751                                        this.scanner.currentPosition - 1));

6760                case TokenNameCharacterLiteral :

6771                                        this.scanner.startPosition,
6772                                        this.scanner.currentPosition - 1));
6773                        break;
6774 
6775                case TokenNameStringLiteral :
6776                        StringLiteral stringLiteral;
6777                        if (this.recordStringLiterals && this.checkExternalizeStrings && !this.statementRecoveryActivated) {

6780                                        this.scanner.startPosition,

6783                                this.compilationUnit.recordStringLiteral(stringLiteral);
6784                        } else {
6785                                stringLiteral = this.createStringLiteral(
6786                                        this.scanner.getCurrentTokenSourceString(),
6787                                        this.scanner.startPosition,
6788                                        this.scanner.currentPosition - 1,
6789                                        0);
6790                        }
6791                        pushOnExpressionStack(stringLiteral);
6792                        break;
6793                case TokenNamefalse :
6794                        pushOnExpressionStack(

6796                        break;

6802                        pushOnExpressionStack(
