6992protected void consumeTypeImportOnDemandDeclarationName() {
6993        // TypeImportOnDemandDeclarationName ::= 'import' Name '.' '*'
6994        /* push an ImportRef build from the last name
6995        stored in the identifier stack. */
6996 
6997        ImportReference impt;
6998        int length;
6999        char[][] tokens = new char[length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--]][];
7000        this.identifierPtr -= length;
7001        long[] positions = new long[length];
7002        System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, length);
7003        System.arraycopy(this.identifierPositionStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, positions, 0, length);
7004        pushOnAstStack(impt = new ImportReference(tokens, positions, true));
7005 
7006        if (this.currentToken == TokenNameSEMICOLON){
7007                impt.declarationSourceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition - 1;
7008        } else {
7009                impt.declarationSourceEnd = impt.sourceEnd;
7010        }
7011        impt.declarationEnd = impt.declarationSourceEnd;
7012        //this.endPosition is just before the ;
7013        impt.declarationSourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
7014 
7015        // recovery
7016        if (this.currentElement != null){
7017                this.lastCheckPoint = impt.declarationSourceEnd+1;
7018                this.currentElement = this.currentElement.add(impt, 0);
7019                this.lastIgnoredToken = -1;
7020                this.restartRecovery = true; // used to avoid branching back into the regular automaton
7021        }
7022}
7023protected void consumeTypeParameterHeader() {
7024        //TypeParameterHeader ::= Identifier
7025        TypeParameter typeParameter = new TypeParameter();
7026        long pos = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr];
7027        final int end = (int) pos;
7028        typeParameter.declarationSourceEnd = end;
7029        typeParameter.sourceEnd = end;
7030        final int start = (int) (pos >>> 32);
7031        typeParameter.declarationSourceStart = start;
7032        typeParameter.sourceStart = start;
7033        typeParameter.name = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr--];
7034        this.identifierLengthPtr--;
7035        pushOnGenericsStack(typeParameter);
7036 
7037        this.listTypeParameterLength++;
7038}

7042protected void consumeTypeParameter1WithExtends() {
7043        //TypeParameter1 ::= TypeParameterHeader 'extends' ReferenceType1
7044        TypeReference superType = (TypeReference) this.genericsStack[this.genericsPtr--];
7045        this.genericsLengthPtr--;
7046        TypeParameter typeParameter = (TypeParameter) this.genericsStack[this.genericsPtr];
7047        typeParameter.declarationSourceEnd = superType.sourceEnd;
7048        typeParameter.type = superType;
7049        superType.bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
7050        this.genericsStack[this.genericsPtr] = typeParameter;
7051}
7052protected void consumeTypeParameter1WithExtendsAndBounds() {
7053        //TypeParameter1 ::= TypeParameterHeader 'extends' ReferenceType AdditionalBoundList1
7054        int additionalBoundsLength = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr--];
7055        TypeReference[] bounds = new TypeReference[additionalBoundsLength];
7056        this.genericsPtr -= additionalBoundsLength;
7057        System.arraycopy(this.genericsStack, this.genericsPtr + 1, bounds, 0, additionalBoundsLength);
7058        TypeReference superType = getTypeReference(this.intStack[this.intPtr--]);
7059        TypeParameter typeParameter = (TypeParameter) this.genericsStack[this.genericsPtr];
7060        typeParameter.declarationSourceEnd = bounds[additionalBoundsLength - 1].sourceEnd;
7061        typeParameter.type = superType;
7062        superType.bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
7063        typeParameter.bounds = bounds;
7064        for (int i = 0, max = bounds.length; i < max; i++) {
7065                bounds[i].bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
7066        }

7076protected void consumeTypeParameters() {
7077        int startPos = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
7078 
7079        if(this.currentElement != null) {
7080                if(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredType) {
7081                        RecoveredType recoveredType =(RecoveredType) this.currentElement;
7082                        int length = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr];
7083                        TypeParameter[] typeParameters = new TypeParameter[length];
7084                        System.arraycopy(this.genericsStack, genericsPtr - length + 1, typeParameters, 0, length);
7085 
7086                        recoveredType.add(typeParameters, startPos);
7087                }
7088        }
7089 
7090 
7091        if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated &&
7092                        options.sourceLevel < ClassFileConstants.JDK1_5&&
7093                        this.lastErrorEndPositionBeforeRecovery < this.scanner.currentPosition) {
7094                int length = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr];
7095                this.problemReporter().invalidUsageOfTypeParameters(
7096                        (TypeParameter) this.genericsStack[genericsPtr - length + 1],
7097                        (TypeParameter) this.genericsStack[genericsPtr]);
7098        }
7099}
7100protected void consumeTypeParameterWithExtends() {
7101        //TypeParameter ::= TypeParameterHeader 'extends' ReferenceType
7102        TypeReference superType = getTypeReference(this.intStack[this.intPtr--]);
7103        TypeParameter typeParameter = (TypeParameter) this.genericsStack[this.genericsPtr];
7104        typeParameter.declarationSourceEnd = superType.sourceEnd;

7108protected void consumeTypeParameterWithExtendsAndBounds() {
7109        //TypeParameter ::= TypeParameterHeader 'extends' ReferenceType AdditionalBoundList
7110        int additionalBoundsLength = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr--];
7111        TypeReference[] bounds = new TypeReference[additionalBoundsLength];
7112        this.genericsPtr -= additionalBoundsLength;
7113        System.arraycopy(this.genericsStack, this.genericsPtr + 1, bounds, 0, additionalBoundsLength);
7114        TypeReference superType = getTypeReference(this.intStack[this.intPtr--]);
7115        TypeParameter typeParameter = (TypeParameter) this.genericsStack[this.genericsPtr];
7116        typeParameter.type = superType;
7117        superType.bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
7118        typeParameter.bounds = bounds;
7119        typeParameter.declarationSourceEnd = bounds[additionalBoundsLength - 1].sourceEnd;
7120        for (int i = 0, max = bounds.length; i < max; i++) {
7121                bounds[i].bits |= ASTNode.IsSuperType;
7122        }

7124protected void consumeUnaryExpression(int op) {
7125        // UnaryExpression ::= '+' PushPosition UnaryExpression
7126        // UnaryExpression ::= '-' PushPosition UnaryExpression
7127        // UnaryExpressionNotPlusMinus ::= '~' PushPosition UnaryExpression
7128        // UnaryExpressionNotPlusMinus ::= '!' PushPosition UnaryExpression
7129 
7130        //optimize the push/pop
7131 
7132        //handle manually the -2147483648 while it is not a real
7133        //computation of an - and 2147483648 (notice that 2147483648
7134        //is Integer.MAX_VALUE+1.....)
7135        //Same for -9223372036854775808L ............
7136 
7137        //this.intStack have the position of the operator
7138 
7139        Expression r, exp = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
7140        if (op == MINUS) {
7141                if ((exp instanceof IntLiteral) && (((IntLiteral) exp).mayRepresentMIN_VALUE())) {
7142                        r = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = new IntLiteralMinValue();
7143                } else {
7144                        if ((exp instanceof LongLiteral) && (((LongLiteral) exp).mayRepresentMIN_VALUE())) {
7145                                r = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = new LongLiteralMinValue();
7146                        } else {
7147                                r = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = new UnaryExpression(exp, op);
7148                        }
7149                }
7150        } else {
7151                r = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] = new UnaryExpression(exp, op);
7152        }
7153        r.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
7154        r.sourceEnd = exp.sourceEnd;
7155}
7156protected void consumeUnaryExpression(int op, boolean post) {
7157        // PreIncrementExpression ::= '++' PushPosition UnaryExpression
7158        // PreDecrementExpression ::= '--' PushPosition UnaryExpression
7159 
7160        // ++ and -- operators
7161        //optimize the push/pop
7162 
7163        //this.intStack has the position of the operator when prefix
7164 
7165        Expression leftHandSide = this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];
7166        if (leftHandSide instanceof Reference) {
7167                // ++foo()++ is unvalid
7168                if (post) {
7169                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
7170                                new PostfixExpression(
7171                                        leftHandSide,
7172                                        IntLiteral.getOne(),
7173                                        op,
7174                                        this.endStatementPosition);
7175                } else {
7176                        this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr] =
7177                                new PrefixExpression(
7178                                        leftHandSide,
7179                                        IntLiteral.getOne(),
7180                                        op,
7181                                        this.intStack[this.intPtr--]);
7182                }
7183        } else {
7184                //the ++ or the -- is NOT taken into account if code gen proceeds
7185                if (!post) {
7186                        this.intPtr--;
7187                }
7188                if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated) problemReporter().invalidUnaryExpression(leftHandSide);
7189        }
7190}

7307/**
7308 * Given the current comment stack, answer whether some comment is available in a certain exclusive range
7309 *
7310 * @param sourceStart int
7311 * @param sourceEnd int
7312 * @return boolean
7313 */
7314public boolean containsComment(int sourceStart, int sourceEnd) {
7315        int iComment = this.scanner.commentPtr;
7316        for (; iComment >= 0; iComment--) {
7317                int commentStart = this.scanner.commentStarts[iComment];
7318                // ignore comments before start
7319                if (commentStart < sourceStart) continue;
7320                // ignore comments after end
7321                if (commentStart > sourceEnd) continue;
7322                return true;
7323        }
7324        return false;
7325}

7383protected void dispatchDeclarationInto(int length) {
7384        /* they are length on this.astStack that should go into
7385           methods fields constructors lists of the typeDecl
7386 
7387           Return if there is a constructor declaration in the methods declaration */
7388 
7389 
7390        // Looks for the size of each array .
7391 
7392        if (length == 0)
7393                return;
7394        int[] flag = new int[length + 1]; //plus one -- see <HERE>
7395        int size1 = 0, size2 = 0, size3 = 0;
7396        boolean hasAbstractMethods = false;
7397        for (int i = length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
7398                ASTNode astNode = this.astStack[this.astPtr--];
7399                if (astNode instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration) {
7400                        //methods and constructors have been regrouped into one single list
7401                        flag[i] = 2;
7402                        size2++;
7403                        if (((AbstractMethodDeclaration) astNode).isAbstract()) {
7404                                hasAbstractMethods = true;
7405                        }
7406                } else if (astNode instanceof TypeDeclaration) {
7407                        flag[i] = 3;
7408                        size3++;
7409                } else {
7410                        //field
7411                        flag[i] = 1;
7412                        size1++;
7413                }
7414        }
7415 
7416        //arrays creation
7417        TypeDeclaration typeDecl = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr];
7418        if (size1 != 0) {
7419                typeDecl.fields = new FieldDeclaration[size1];
7420        }
7421        if (size2 != 0) {
7422                typeDecl.methods = new AbstractMethodDeclaration[size2];
7423                if (hasAbstractMethods) typeDecl.bits |= ASTNode.HasAbstractMethods;
7424        }
7425        if (size3 != 0) {
7426                typeDecl.memberTypes = new TypeDeclaration[size3];
7427        }
7428 
7429        //arrays fill up
7430        size1 = size2 = size3 = 0;
7431        int flagI = flag[0], start = 0;
7432        int length2;
7433        for (int end = 0; end <= length; end++) //<HERE> the plus one allows to
7434                {
7435                if (flagI != flag[end]) //treat the last element as a ended flag.....
7436                        { //array copy
7437                        switch (flagI) {
7438                                case 1 :
7439                                        size1 += (length2 = end - start);
7440                                        System.arraycopy(
7441                                                this.astStack,
7442                                                this.astPtr + start + 1,
7443                                                typeDecl.fields,
7444                                                size1 - length2,
7445                                                length2);
7446                                        break;
7447                                case 2 :
7448                                        size2 += (length2 = end - start);
7449                                        System.arraycopy(
7450                                                this.astStack,
7451                                                this.astPtr + start + 1,
7452                                                typeDecl.methods,
7453                                                size2 - length2,
7454                                                length2);
7455                                        break;
7456                                case 3 :
7457                                        size3 += (length2 = end - start);
7458                                        System.arraycopy(
7459                                                this.astStack,
7460                                                this.astPtr + start + 1,
7461                                                typeDecl.memberTypes,
7462                                                size3 - length2,
7463                                                length2);
7464                                        break;
7465                        }
7466                        flagI = flag[start = end];
7467                }
7468        }
7469 
7470        if (typeDecl.memberTypes != null) {
7471                for (int i = typeDecl.memberTypes.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
7472                        typeDecl.memberTypes[i].enclosingType = typeDecl;
7473                }
7474        }
7475}
7476protected void dispatchDeclarationIntoEnumDeclaration(int length) {
7477

7479      return;
7480   int[] flag = new int[length + 1]; //plus one -- see <HERE>
7481   int size1 = 0, size2 = 0, size3 = 0;
7482   TypeDeclaration enumDeclaration = (TypeDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr - length];
7483   boolean hasAbstractMethods = false;

7486      if (astNode instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration) {
7487         //methods and constructors have been regrouped into one single list
7488         flag[i] = 2;

7491                        hasAbstractMethods = true;
7492                }

7494         flag[i] = 3;
7495         size3++;
7496      } else if (astNode instanceof FieldDeclaration) {
7497         flag[i] = 1;
7498         size1++;
7499//         if(astNode instanceof EnumConstant) {
7500//            EnumConstant constant = (EnumConstant) astNode;
7501//            ((AllocationExpression)constant.initialization).type = new SingleTypeReference(enumDeclaration.name,
7502//                  (((long) enumDeclaration.sourceStart) << 32) + enumDeclaration.sourceEnd);
7503//         }
7504      }
7505   }
7506 
7507   //arrays creation
7508   if (size1 != 0) {
7509      enumDeclaration.fields = new FieldDeclaration[size1];
7510   }

7512      enumDeclaration.methods = new AbstractMethodDeclaration[size2];
7513      if (hasAbstractMethods) enumDeclaration.bits |= ASTNode.HasAbstractMethods;
7514   }
7515   if (size3 != 0) {
7516      enumDeclaration.memberTypes = new TypeDeclaration[size3];
7517   }
7518 
7519   //arrays fill up
7520   size1 = size2 = size3 = 0;
7521   int flagI = flag[0], start = 0;
7522   int length2;
7523   for (int end = 0; end <= length; end++) //<HERE> the plus one allows to
7524      {
7525      if (flagI != flag[end]) //treat the last element as a ended flag.....
7526         { //array copy
7527         switch (flagI) {
7528            case 1 :
7529               size1 += (length2 = end - start);
7530               System.arraycopy(
7531                  this.astStack,
7532                  this.astPtr + start + 1,
7533                  enumDeclaration.fields,
7534                  size1 - length2,
7535                  length2);
7536               break;
7537            case 2 :
7538               size2 += (length2 = end - start);
7539               System.arraycopy(
7540                  this.astStack,
7541                  this.astPtr + start + 1,
7542                  enumDeclaration.methods,
7543                  size2 - length2,
7544                  length2);
7545               break;
7546            case 3 :
7547               size3 += (length2 = end - start);
7548               System.arraycopy(
7549                  this.astStack,
7550                  this.astPtr + start + 1,
7551                  enumDeclaration.memberTypes,
7552                  size3 - length2,
7553                  length2);
7554               break;
7555         }
7556         flagI = flag[start = end];
7557      }
7558   }
7559 
7560   if (enumDeclaration.memberTypes != null) {
7561      for (int i = enumDeclaration.memberTypes.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
7562         enumDeclaration.memberTypes[i].enclosingType = enumDeclaration;
7563      }
7564   }}
7565protected CompilationUnitDeclaration endParse(int act) {
7566 
7567        this.lastAct = act;
7568 
7569        if(this.statementRecoveryActivated ) {
7570                RecoveredElement recoveredElement = this.buildInitialRecoveryState();
7571                recoveredElement.topElement().updateParseTree();
7572                if(this.hasError) this.resetStacks();
7573        } else if (this.currentElement != null){
7574                if (VERBOSE_RECOVERY){
7575                        System.out.print(Messages.parser_syntaxRecovery);
7576                        System.out.println("--------------------------");                 //$NON-NLS-1$
7577                        System.out.println(this.compilationUnit);
7578                        System.out.println("----------------------------------"); //$NON-NLS-1$
7579                }
7580                recoverAST(this.currentElement);
7581                this.currentElement.topElement().updateParseTree();
7582        } else {
7583                if (this.diet & VERBOSE_RECOVERY){
7584                        System.out.print(Messages.parser_regularParse);
7585                        System.out.println("--------------------------");         //$NON-NLS-1$
7586                        System.out.println(this.compilationUnit);
7587                        System.out.println("----------------------------------"); //$NON-NLS-1$
7588                }
7589        }
7590        persistLineSeparatorPositions();
7591        for (int i = 0; i < this.scanner.foundTaskCount; i++){
7592                if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated) problemReporter().task(
7593                        new String(this.scanner.foundTaskTags[i]),
7594                        new String(this.scanner.foundTaskMessages[i]),
7595                        this.scanner.foundTaskPriorities[i] == null ? null : new String(this.scanner.foundTaskPriorities[i]),
7596                        this.scanner.foundTaskPositions[i][0],
7597                        this.scanner.foundTaskPositions[i][1]);
7598        }
7599        if (this.compilationUnit.statements==null)
7600                this.compilationUnit.statements=new ProgramElement[0];
7601        return this.compilationUnit;
7602}
7603/*
7604 * Flush comments defined prior to a given positions.
7605 *
7606 * Note: comments are stacked in syntactical order
7607 *
7608 * Either answer given <position>, or the end position of a comment line
7609 * immediately following the <position> (same line)
7610 *
7611 * e.g.
7612 * void foo(){
7613 * } // end of method foo
7614 */
7615 
7616public int flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(int position) {
7617 
7618        int lastCommentIndex = this.scanner.commentPtr;
7619        if (lastCommentIndex < 0) return position; // no comment
7620 
7621        // compute the index of the first obsolete comment
7622        int index = lastCommentIndex;
7623        int validCount = 0;
7624        while (index >= 0){
7625                int commentEnd = this.scanner.commentStops[index];
7626                if (commentEnd < 0) commentEnd = -commentEnd; // negative end position for non-javadoc comments
7627                if (commentEnd <= position){
7628                        break;
7629                }
7630                index--;
7631                validCount++;
7632        }
7633        // if the source at <position> is immediately followed by a line comment, then
7634        // flush this comment and shift <position> to the comment end.
7635        if (validCount > 0){
7636                int immediateCommentEnd = -this.scanner.commentStops[index+1]; //non-javadoc comment end positions are negative
7637                if (immediateCommentEnd > 0){ // only tolerating non-javadoc comments
7638                        // is there any line break until the end of the immediate comment ? (thus only tolerating line comment)
7639                        immediateCommentEnd--; // comment end in one char too far
7640                        if (Util.getLineNumber(position, this.scanner.lineEnds, 0, this.scanner.linePtr)
7641                                        == Util.getLineNumber(immediateCommentEnd, this.scanner.lineEnds, 0, this.scanner.linePtr)){
7642                                position = immediateCommentEnd;
7643                                validCount--; // flush this comment
7644                                index++;
7645                        }
7646                }
7647        }
7648 
7649        if (index < 0) return position; // no obsolete comment
7650 
7651        switch (validCount) {
7652                case 0:
7653                        // do nothing
7654                        break;
7655                // move valid comment infos, overriding obsolete comment infos
7656                case 2:
7657                        this.scanner.commentStarts[0] = this.scanner.commentStarts[index+1];
7658                        this.scanner.commentStops[0] = this.scanner.commentStops[index+1];
7659                        this.scanner.commentTagStarts[0] = this.scanner.commentTagStarts[index+1];
7660                        this.scanner.commentStarts[1] = this.scanner.commentStarts[index+2];
7661                        this.scanner.commentStops[1] = this.scanner.commentStops[index+2];
7662                        this.scanner.commentTagStarts[1] = this.scanner.commentTagStarts[index+2];
7663                        break;
7664                case 1:
7665                        this.scanner.commentStarts[0] = this.scanner.commentStarts[index+1];
7666                        this.scanner.commentStops[0] = this.scanner.commentStops[index+1];
7667                        this.scanner.commentTagStarts[0] = this.scanner.commentTagStarts[index+1];
7668                        break;
7669                default:
7670                        System.arraycopy(this.scanner.commentStarts, index + 1, this.scanner.commentStarts, 0, validCount);
7671                        System.arraycopy(this.scanner.commentStops, index + 1, this.scanner.commentStops, 0, validCount);
7672                        System.arraycopy(this.scanner.commentTagStarts, index + 1, this.scanner.commentTagStarts, 0, validCount);
7673        }
7674        this.scanner.commentPtr = validCount - 1;
7675        return position;
7676}
7677protected TypeReference getAnnotationType() {
7678        int length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--];
7679        if (length == 1) {
7680                return new SingleTypeReference(
7681                                this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
7682                                this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
7683        } else {
7684                char[][] tokens = new char[length][];
7685                this.identifierPtr -= length;
7686                long[] positions = new long[length];
7687                System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, length);
7688                System.arraycopy(
7689                        this.identifierPositionStack,
7690                        this.identifierPtr + 1,
7691                        positions,
7692                        0,
7693                        length);
7694                return new QualifiedTypeReference(tokens, positions);
7695        }
7696}
7697public int getFirstToken() {
7698        // the first token is a virtual token that
7699        // allows the parser to parse several goals
7700        // even if they aren't LALR(1)....
7701        // Goal ::= '++' JavaScriptUnit
7702        // Goal ::= '--' MethodBody
7703        // Goal ::= '==' ConstructorBody
7704        // -- Initializer
7705        // Goal ::= '>>' StaticInitializer
7706        // Goal ::= '>>' Block
7707        // -- error recovery
7708        // Goal ::= '>>>' Headers
7709        // Goal ::= '*' BlockStatements
7710        // Goal ::= '*' MethodPushModifiersHeader
7711        // -- JDOM
7712        // Goal ::= '&&' FieldDeclaration
7713        // Goal ::= '||' ImportDeclaration
7714        // Goal ::= '?' PackageDeclaration
7715        // Goal ::= '+' TypeDeclaration
7716        // Goal ::= '/' GenericMethodDeclaration
7717        // Goal ::= '&' ClassBodyDeclaration
7718        // -- code snippet
7719        // Goal ::= '%' Expression
7720        // -- completion parser
7721        // Goal ::= '!' ConstructorBlockStatementsopt
7722        // Goal ::= '~' BlockStatementsopt
7723 
7724        return this.firstToken;
7725}
7726/*
7727 * Answer back an array of sourceStart/sourceEnd positions of the available JavaDoc comments.
7728 * The array is a flattened structure: 2*n entries with consecutives start and end positions.
7729 *
7730 * If no JavaDoc is available, then null is answered instead of an empty array.
7731 *
7732 * e.g. { 10, 20, 25, 45 }  --> javadoc1 from 10 to 20, javadoc2 from 25 to 45
7733 */
7734public int[] getJavaDocPositions() {
7735 
7736        int javadocCount = 0;
7737        for (int i = 0, max = this.scanner.commentPtr; i <= max; i++){
7738                // javadoc only (non javadoc comment have negative end positions.)
7739                if (this.scanner.commentStops[i] > 0){
7740                        javadocCount++;
7741                }
7742        }
7743        if (javadocCount == 0) return null;
7744 
7745        int[] positions = new int[2*javadocCount];
7746        int index = 0;
7747        for (int i = 0, max = this.scanner.commentPtr; i <= max; i++){
7748                // javadoc only (non javadoc comment have negative end positions.)
7749                if (this.scanner.commentStops[i] > 0){
7750                        positions[index++] = this.scanner.commentStarts[i];
7751                        positions[index++] = this.scanner.commentStops[i]-1; //stop is one over
7752                }
7753        }
7754        return positions;
7755}
7756        public void getMethodBodies(CompilationUnitDeclaration unit) {
7757                //fill the methods bodies in order for the code to be generated
7758 
7759                if (unit == null) return;
7760 
7761                if (unit.ignoreMethodBodies) {
7762                        unit.ignoreFurtherInvestigation = true;
7763                        return;
7764                        // if initial diet parse did not work, no need to dig into method bodies.
7765                }
7766 
7767                if ((unit.bits & ASTNode.HasAllMethodBodies) != 0)
7768                        return; //work already done ...
7769 
7770                // save existing values to restore them at the end of the parsing process
7771                // see bug 47079 for more details
7772                int[] oldLineEnds = this.scanner.lineEnds;
7773                int oldLinePtr = this.scanner.linePtr;
7774 
7775                //real parse of the method....
7776                CompilationResult compilationResult = unit.compilationResult;
7777                char[] contents = compilationResult.compilationUnit.getContents();
7778                this.scanner.setSource(contents, compilationResult);
7779 
7780                if (this.javadocParser != null && this.javadocParser.checkDocComment) {
7781                        this.javadocParser.scanner.setSource(contents);
7782                }
7783                if (unit.types != null) {
7784                        for (int i = unit.types.length; --i >= 0;)
7785                                unit.types[i].parseMethod(this, unit);
7786                }
7787 
7788                // tag unit has having read bodies
7789                unit.bits |= ASTNode.HasAllMethodBodies;
7790 
7791                // this is done to prevent any side effects on the compilation unit result
7792                // line separator positions array.
7793                this.scanner.lineEnds = oldLineEnds;
7794                this.scanner.linePtr = oldLinePtr;
7795        }
7796protected char getNextCharacter(char[] comment, int[] index) {
7797        char nextCharacter = comment[index[0]++];
7798        switch(nextCharacter) {
7799                case '\\' :
7800                        int c1, c2, c3, c4;
7801                        index[0]++;
7802                        while (comment[index[0]] == 'u') index[0]++;
7803                        if (!(((c1 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(comment[index[0]++])) > 15
7804                                || c1 < 0)
7805                                || ((c2 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(comment[index[0]++])) > 15 || c2 < 0)
7806                                || ((c3 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(comment[index[0]++])) > 15 || c3 < 0)
7807                                || ((c4 = ScannerHelper.getNumericValue(comment[index[0]++])) > 15 || c4 < 0))) {
7808                                        nextCharacter = (char) (((c1 * 16 + c2) * 16 + c3) * 16 + c4);
7809                        }
7810                        break;
7811        }
7812        return nextCharacter;
7813}
7814protected Expression getTypeReference(Expression exp) {
7815 
7816        exp.bits &= ~ASTNode.RestrictiveFlagMASK;
7817        exp.bits |= Binding.TYPE;
7818        return exp;
7819}
7820protected TypeReference getTypeReference(int dim) {
7821        /* build a Reference on a variable that may be qualified or not
7822         This variable is a type reference and dim will be its dimensions*/
7823 
7824        TypeReference ref;
7825        int length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--];
7826        if (length < 0) { //flag for precompiled type reference on base types
7827                ref = TypeReference.baseTypeReference(-length, dim);
7828                ref.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
7829                if (dim == 0) {
7830                        ref.sourceEnd = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
7831                } else {
7832                        this.intPtr--;
7833                        ref.sourceEnd = this.endPosition;
7834                }
7835        } else {
7836                int numberOfIdentifiers = this.genericsIdentifiersLengthStack[this.genericsIdentifiersLengthPtr--];
7837                if (length != numberOfIdentifiers || this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr] != 0) {
7838                        // generic type
7839                        ref = getTypeReferenceForGenericType(dim, length, numberOfIdentifiers);
7840                } else if (length == 1) {
7841                        // single variable reference
7842                        this.genericsLengthPtr--; // pop the 0
7843                        if (dim == 0) {
7844                                ref =
7845                                        new SingleTypeReference(
7846                                                this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
7847                                                this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
7848                        } else {
7849                                ref =
7850                                        new ArrayTypeReference(
7851                                                this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
7852                                                dim,
7853                                                this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
7854                                ref.sourceEnd = this.endPosition;
7855                        }
7856                } else {
7857                        this.genericsLengthPtr--;
7858                        //Qualified variable reference
7859                        char[][] tokens = new char[length][];
7860                        this.identifierPtr -= length;
7861                        long[] positions = new long[length];
7862                        System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, length);
7863                        System.arraycopy(
7864                                this.identifierPositionStack,
7865                                this.identifierPtr + 1,
7866                                positions,
7867                                0,
7868                                length);
7869                        if (dim == 0) {
7870                                ref = new QualifiedTypeReference(tokens, positions);
7871                        } else {
7872                                ref = new ArrayQualifiedTypeReference(tokens, dim, positions);
7873                                ref.sourceEnd = this.endPosition;
7874                        }
7875                }
7876        }
7877        return ref;
7878}
7879protected TypeReference getTypeReferenceForGenericType(int dim, int identifierLength, int numberOfIdentifiers) {
7880        if (identifierLength == 1 && numberOfIdentifiers == 1) {
7881                int currentTypeArgumentsLength = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr--];
7882                TypeReference[] typeArguments = new TypeReference[currentTypeArgumentsLength];
7883                this.genericsPtr -= currentTypeArgumentsLength;
7884                System.arraycopy(this.genericsStack, this.genericsPtr + 1, typeArguments, 0, currentTypeArgumentsLength);
7885                ParameterizedSingleTypeReference parameterizedSingleTypeReference = new ParameterizedSingleTypeReference(this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr], typeArguments, dim, this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
7886                if (dim != 0) {
7887                        parameterizedSingleTypeReference.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
7888                }
7889                return parameterizedSingleTypeReference;
7890        } else {
7891                TypeReference[][] typeArguments = new TypeReference[numberOfIdentifiers][];
7892                char[][] tokens = new char[numberOfIdentifiers][];
7893                long[] positions = new long[numberOfIdentifiers];
7894                int index = numberOfIdentifiers;
7895                int currentIdentifiersLength = identifierLength;
7896                while (index > 0) {
7897                        int currentTypeArgumentsLength = this.genericsLengthStack[this.genericsLengthPtr--];
7898                        if (currentTypeArgumentsLength != 0) {
7899                                this.genericsPtr -= currentTypeArgumentsLength;
7900                                System.arraycopy(this.genericsStack, this.genericsPtr + 1, typeArguments[index - 1] = new TypeReference[currentTypeArgumentsLength], 0, currentTypeArgumentsLength);
7901                        }
7902                        switch(currentIdentifiersLength) {
7903                                case 1 :
7904                                        // we are in a case A<B>.C<D> or A<B>.C<D>
7905                                        tokens[index - 1] = this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr];
7906                                        positions[index - 1] = this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--];
7907                                        break;
7908                                default:
7909                                        // we are in a case A.B.C<B>.C<D> or A.B.C<B>...
7910                                        this.identifierPtr -= currentIdentifiersLength;
7911                                        System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, index - currentIdentifiersLength, currentIdentifiersLength);
7912                                        System.arraycopy(this.identifierPositionStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, positions, index - currentIdentifiersLength, currentIdentifiersLength);
7913                        }
7914                        index -= currentIdentifiersLength;
7915                        if (index > 0) {
7916                                currentIdentifiersLength = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--];
7917                        }
7918                }
7919                ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference parameterizedQualifiedTypeReference = new ParameterizedQualifiedTypeReference(tokens, typeArguments, dim, positions);
7920                if (dim != 0) {
7921                        parameterizedQualifiedTypeReference.sourceEnd = this.endStatementPosition;
7922                }
7923                return parameterizedQualifiedTypeReference;
7924        }
7925}
7926protected NameReference getUnspecifiedReference() {
7927        /* build a (unspecified) NameReference which may be qualified*/
7928 
7929        int length;
7930        NameReference ref;
7931        if ((length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--]) == 1)
7932                // single variable reference
7933                ref =
7934                        new SingleNameReference(
7935                                this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
7936                                this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
7937        else
7938                //Qualified variable reference
7939                {
7940                char[][] tokens = new char[length][];
7941                this.identifierPtr -= length;
7942                System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, length);
7943                long[] positions = new long[length];
7944                System.arraycopy(this.identifierPositionStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, positions, 0, length);
7945                ref =
7946                        new QualifiedNameReference(tokens,
7947                                positions,
7948                                (int) (this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr + 1] >> 32), // sourceStart
7949                                (int) this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr + length]); // sourceEnd
7950        }
7951        return ref;
7952}
7953protected NameReference getUnspecifiedReferenceOptimized() {
7954        /* build a (unspecified) NameReference which may be qualified
7955        The optimization occurs for qualified reference while we are
7956        certain in this case the last item of the qualified name is
7957        a field access. This optimization is IMPORTANT while it results
7958        that when a NameReference is build, the type checker should always
7959        look for that it is not a type reference */
7960 
7961        int length;
7962        NameReference ref;
7963        if ((length = this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr--]) == 1) {
7964                // single variable reference
7965                ref =
7966                        new SingleNameReference(
7967                                this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr],
7968                                this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr--]);
7969                ref.bits &= ~ASTNode.RestrictiveFlagMASK;
7970                ref.bits |= Binding.LOCAL | Binding.FIELD;
7971                return ref;
7972        }
7973 
7974        //Qualified-variable-reference
7975        //In fact it is variable-reference DOT field-ref , but it would result in a type
7976        //conflict tha can be only reduce by making a superclass (or inetrface ) between
7977        //nameReference and FiledReference or putting FieldReference under NameReference
7978        //or else..........This optimisation is not really relevant so just leave as it is
7979 
7980        char[][] tokens = new char[length][];
7981        this.identifierPtr -= length;
7982        System.arraycopy(this.identifierStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, tokens, 0, length);
7983        long[] positions = new long[length];
7984        System.arraycopy(this.identifierPositionStack, this.identifierPtr + 1, positions, 0, length);
7985        ref = new QualifiedNameReference(
7986                        tokens,
7987                        positions,
7988                        (int) (this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr + 1] >> 32), // sourceStart
7989                        (int) this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr + length]); // sourceEnd
7990        ref.bits &= ~ASTNode.RestrictiveFlagMASK;
7991        ref.bits |= Binding.LOCAL | Binding.FIELD;
7992        return ref;
7993}

8061public void goForInitializer(){
8062        //tells the scanner to go for initializer parsing
8063 
8064        this.firstToken = TokenNameRIGHT_SHIFT ;

8091protected void ignoreExpressionAssignment() {
8092        // Assignment ::= InvalidArrayInitializerAssignement
8093        // encoded operator would be: this.intStack[this.intPtr]
8094        this.intPtr--;
8095        ArrayInitializer arrayInitializer = (ArrayInitializer) this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr--];
8096        this.expressionLengthPtr -- ;
8097        // report a syntax error and abort parsing
8098        if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated) problemReporter().arrayConstantsOnlyInArrayInitializers(arrayInitializer.sourceStart, arrayInitializer.sourceEnd);
8099}

8103public void initialize(boolean initializeNLS) {
8104        //positionning the parser for a new compilation unit
8105        //avoiding stack reallocation and all that....
8106        this.astPtr = -1;
8107        this.astLengthPtr = -1;
8108        this.expressionPtr = -1;
8109        this.expressionLengthPtr = -1;
8110        this.identifierPtr = -1;
8111        this.identifierLengthPtr        = -1;
8112        this.intPtr = -1;
8113        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType = 0] = 0; // need to reset for further reuse
8114        this.variablesCounter[this.nestedType] = 0;
8115        this.dimensions = 0 ;
8116        this.realBlockPtr = 0;
8117        this.compilationUnit = null;
8118        this.referenceContext = null;
8119        this.endStatementPosition = 0;
8120 
8121        //remove objects from stack too, while the same parser/compiler couple is
8122        //re-used between two compilations ....
8123 
8124        int astLength = this.astStack.length;
8125        if (this.noAstNodes.length < astLength){
8126                this.noAstNodes = new ASTNode[astLength];
8127                //System.out.println("Resized AST stacks : "+ astLength);
8128

8134                this.noExpressions = new Expression[expressionLength];
8135                //System.out.println("Resized EXPR stacks : "+ expressionLength);
8136        }
8137        System.arraycopy(this.noExpressions, 0, this.expressionStack, 0, expressionLength);
8138 
8139        // reset this.scanner state
8140        this.scanner.commentPtr = -1;
8141        this.scanner.foundTaskCount = 0;
8142        this.scanner.eofPosition = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
8143        this.recordStringLiterals = true;
8144        final boolean checkNLS = this.options.getSeverity(CompilerOptions.NonExternalizedString) != ProblemSeverities.Ignore;
8145        this.checkExternalizeStrings = checkNLS;
8146        this.scanner.checkNonExternalizedStringLiterals = initializeNLS && checkNLS;
8147 
8148        resetModifiers();
8149 
8150        // recovery
8151        this.lastCheckPoint = -1;
8152        this.currentElement = null;
8153        this.restartRecovery = false;
8154        this.hasReportedError = false;
8155        this.recoveredStaticInitializerStart = 0;

8185public void jumpOverMethodBody() {
8186        //on diet parsing.....do not buffer method statements
8187 
8188        //the scanner.diet is reinitialized to false
8189        //automatically by the scanner once it has jumped over
8190        //the statements
8191 
8192        if (this.diet && (this.dietInt == 0))
8193                this.scanner.diet = true;

8195private void jumpOverType(){
8196        if (this.recoveredTypes != null && this.nextTypeStart > -1 && this.nextTypeStart < this.scanner.currentPosition) {
8197 
8198                if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8199                        System.out.println("Jump         -"); //$NON-NLS-1$
8200                }
8201 
8202                TypeDeclaration typeDeclaration = this.recoveredTypes[this.recoveredTypePtr];
8203                boolean isAnonymous = typeDeclaration.allocation != null;
8204 
8205                int end = this.scanner.eofPosition;
8206                this.scanner.resetTo(typeDeclaration.declarationSourceEnd + 1, end  - 1);
8207                if(!isAnonymous) {
8208                        ((RecoveryScanner)this.scanner).setPendingTokens(new int[]{TokenNameSEMICOLON, TokenNamebreak});
8209                } else {
8210                        ((RecoveryScanner)this.scanner).setPendingTokens(new int[]{TokenNameIdentifier, TokenNameEQUAL, TokenNameIdentifier});
8211                }
8212 
8213                this.pendingRecoveredType = typeDeclaration;
8214 
8215                try {
8216                        this.currentToken = this.scanner.getNextToken();
8217                } catch(InvalidInputException e){
8218                        // it's impossible because we added pending tokens before
8219                }
8220 
8221                if(++this.recoveredTypePtr < this.recoveredTypes.length) {
8222                        TypeDeclaration nextTypeDeclaration = this.recoveredTypes[this.recoveredTypePtr];
8223                        this.nextTypeStart =
8224                                nextTypeDeclaration.allocation == null
8225                                        ? nextTypeDeclaration.declarationSourceStart
8226                                                        : nextTypeDeclaration.allocation.sourceStart;
8227                } else {
8228                        this.nextTypeStart = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
8229                }
8230        }
8231}
8232protected void markEnclosingMemberWithLocalType() {
8233                if (this.currentElement != null) return; // this is already done in the recovery code
8234                for (int i = this.astPtr; i >= 0; i--) {
8235                        ASTNode node = this.astStack[i];
8236                        if (node instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration
8237                                        || node instanceof FieldDeclaration
8238                                        || (node instanceof TypeDeclaration // mark type for now: all initializers will be marked when added to this type
8239                                                        // and enclosing type must not be closed (see https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=147485)
8240                                                        && ((TypeDeclaration) node).declarationSourceEnd == 0)) {
8241                                node.bits |= ASTNode.HasLocalType;
8242                                return;
8243                        }
8244                }
8245                // default to reference context (case of parse method body)
8246                if (this.referenceContext instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration
8247                                || this.referenceContext instanceof TypeDeclaration) {
8248                        ((ASTNode)this.referenceContext).bits |= ASTNode.HasLocalType;
8249                }

8251protected void markInitializersWithLocalType(TypeDeclaration type) {
8252        if (type.fields == null || (type.bits & ASTNode.HasLocalType) == 0) return;
8253        for (int i = 0, length = type.fields.length; i < length; i++) {
8254                FieldDeclaration field = type.fields[i];
8255                if (field instanceof Initializer) {
8256                        field.bits |= ASTNode.HasLocalType;
8257                }
8258        }

8381protected MessageSend newMessageSend() {
8382        // '(' ArgumentListopt ')'
8383        // the arguments are on the expression stack
8384 
8385        MessageSend m = new MessageSend();
8386        int length;
8387        if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
8388                this.expressionPtr -= length;
8389                System.arraycopy(
8390                        this.expressionStack,
8391                        this.expressionPtr + 1,
8392                        m.arguments = new Expression[length],
8393                        0,
8394                        length);
8395        }
8396        return m;
8397}
8398protected MessageSend newMessageSendWithTypeArguments() {
8399        MessageSend m = new MessageSend();
8400        int length;
8401        if ((length = this.expressionLengthStack[this.expressionLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
8402                this.expressionPtr -= length;
8403                System.arraycopy(
8404                        this.expressionStack,
8405                        this.expressionPtr + 1,
8406                        m.arguments = new Expression[length],
8407                        0,
8408                        length);
8409        }

8412protected void optimizedConcatNodeLists() {
8413        /*back from a recursive loop. Virtualy group the
8414        astNode into an array using this.astLengthStack*/
8415 
8416        /*
8417         * This is a case where you have two sublists into the this.astStack that you want
8418         * to merge in one list. There is no action required on the this.astStack. The only
8419         * thing you need to do is merge the two lengths specified on the astStackLength.
8420         * The top two length are for example:
8421         * ... p   n
8422         * and you want to result in a list like:
8423         * ... n+p
8424         * This means that the p could be equals to 0 in case there is no astNode pushed
8425         * on the this.astStack.
8426         * Look at the InterfaceMemberDeclarations for an example.
8427         * This case optimizes the fact that p == 1.
8428         */
8429 
8430        this.astLengthStack[--this.astLengthPtr]++;
8431}

8433protected boolean isErrorState(int act) {
8434         int stackTop=this.stateStackTop;
8435         int [] tempStack=new int[this.stack.length+2];
8436         System.arraycopy(this.stack, 0, tempStack, 0, this.stack.length);
8437        boolean first=true;
8438        ProcessTerminals : for (;;) {
8439                int stackLength = tempStack.length;
8440                if (!first)
8441                {
8442                  if (++stackTop >= stackLength) {
8443                        System.arraycopy(
8444                                        tempStack, 0,
8445                                        tempStack = new int[stackLength + StackIncrement], 0,
8446                                stackLength);
8447                   }
8448                  tempStack[stackTop] = act;
8449                }
8450          first=false;
8451                act = tAction(act, this.currentToken);
8452                if (act == ERROR_ACTION ) {
8453                        return true;
8454                }
8455                if (act <= NUM_RULES) {
8456                        stackTop--;
8457 
8458                } else if (act > ERROR_ACTION) { /* shift-reduce */
8459                        if (DEBUG) System.out.println("<<shift-reduce consume Token: "+scanner.toStringAction(this.currentToken)); //$NON-NLS-1$
8460                        return false;
8461//                        consumeToken(this.currentToken);
8462//                        if (this.currentElement != null) this.recoveryTokenCheck();
8463//                        try {
8464//                                prevPos = scanner.currentPosition;
8465//                                prevToken = currentToken;
8466//                                insertedSemicolon = false;
8467//                                this.currentToken = this.scanner.getNextToken();
8468//                                if (DEBUG) System.out.println(">>shift-reduce Next Token: "+scanner.dumpCurrent());
8469//                        } catch(InvalidInputException e){
8470//                                if (!this.hasReportedError){
8471//                                        this.problemReporter().scannerError(this, e.getMessage());
8472//                                        this.hasReportedError = true;
8473//                                }
8474//                                this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.currentPosition;
8475//                                this.restartRecovery = true;
8476//                        }
8477//                        if(this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
8478//                                jumpOverTypeAfterReduce = true;
8479//                        }
8480//                        act -= ERROR_ACTION;
8481 
8482                } else {
8483                    if (act < ACCEPT_ACTION) { /* shift */
8484                                if (DEBUG) System.out.println("<<shift consume Token: "+scanner.toStringAction(this.currentToken)); //$NON-NLS-1$
8485                                return false;
8486//                                consumeToken(this.currentToken);
8487//                                if (this.currentElement != null) this.recoveryTokenCheck();
8488//                                try{
8489//                                        prevPos = scanner.currentPosition;
8490//                                        prevToken = currentToken;
8491//                                        insertedSemicolon = false;
8492//                                        this.currentToken = this.scanner.getNextToken();
8493//                                        if (DEBUG) System.out.println(">>shift next Token: "+scanner.dumpCurrent());
8494//                                } catch(InvalidInputException e){
8495//                                        if (!this.hasReportedError){
8496//                                                this.problemReporter().scannerError(this, e.getMessage());
8497//                                                this.hasReportedError = true;
8498//                                        }
8499//                                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.currentPosition;
8500//                                        this.restartRecovery = true;
8501//                                }
8502//                                if(this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
8503//                                        this.jumpOverType();

8508                }
8509 
8510                // ProcessNonTerminals :
8511                do { /* reduce */
8512                        stackTop -= (rhs[act] - 1);
8513                        act = ntAction(tempStack[stackTop], lhs[act]);
8514                } while (act <= NUM_RULES);
8515        }
8516return false;

8518 
8519 
8520/*main loop of the automat
8521When a rule is reduced, the method consumeRule(int) is called with the number
8522of the consumed rule. When a terminal is consumed, the method consumeToken(int) is
8523called in order to remember (when needed) the consumed token */
8524// (int)asr[asi(act)]
8525// name[symbol_index[currentKind]]
8526protected void parse() {
8527        if (DEBUG) System.out.println("-- ENTER INSIDE PARSE METHOD --");  //$NON-NLS-1$
8528 
8529        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8530                System.out.println("- Start --------------------------------");  //$NON-NLS-1$
8531        }
8532 
8533        boolean isDietParse = this.diet;
8534        int oldFirstToken = getFirstToken();
8535        this.hasError = false;
8536 
8537        this.hasReportedError = false;
8538        boolean insertedSemicolon = false;
8539        int prevAct = START_STATE,
8540                prevToken = getFirstToken(),
8541                prevPos = scanner.startPosition;
8542 
8543        int act = START_STATE;
8544        this.stateStackTop = -1;
8545        this.currentToken = getFirstToken();
8546        ProcessTerminals : for (;;) {
8547                int stackLength = this.stack.length;
8548                if (++this.stateStackTop >= stackLength) {
8549                        System.arraycopy(
8550                                this.stack, 0,
8551                                this.stack = new int[stackLength + StackIncrement], 0,
8552                                stackLength);
8553                }
8554                this.stack[this.stateStackTop] = act;
8555 
8556                if (DEBUG)
8557                        System.out.println("action="+act+ ((term_check[base_action[act]+this.currentToken] == this.currentToken)?"":" - take default") ); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$
8558                prevAct=act;
8559 
8560                if (optionalSemicolonState[act])
8561                {
8562                        if (term_check[base_action[act]+this.currentToken] != this.currentToken)
8563                        {
8564                                if (isErrorState(act))
8565                                {
8566                                  if (!insertedSemicolon && shouldInsertSemicolon(prevPos, prevToken) )
8567                                  {
8568                                        currentToken = TokenNameSEMICOLON;
8569                                        this.insertedSemicolonPosition=prevPos;
8570                                        scanner.pushBack();
8571                                        insertedSemicolon = true;
8572 
8573                                  }
8574                                }
8575                        }
8576                }
8577 
8578                act = tAction(act, this.currentToken);
8579                if (act == ERROR_ACTION || this.restartRecovery) {
8580//                        if ( act == ERROR_ACTION &&
8581//                                        !insertedSemicolon &&
8582//                                        shouldInsertSemicolon(prevPos, prevToken)
8583//                                        ) {
8584//                                        act = prevAct;
8585//                                        --stateStackTop;
8586//                                        currentToken = TokenNameSEMICOLON;
8587//                                        scanner.pushBack();
8588//                                        insertedSemicolon = true;
8589//                                        continue ProcessTerminals;
8590//                                }
8591 
8592                        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8593                                if (this.restartRecovery) {
8594                                        System.out.println("Restart      - "); //$NON-NLS-1$
8595                                } else {
8596                                        System.out.println("Error        - "); //$NON-NLS-1$
8597                                }
8598                        }
8599 
8600                        int errorPos = this.scanner.currentPosition;
8601                        if (!this.hasReportedError) {
8602                                this.hasError = true;
8603                        }
8604                         if (resumeOnSyntaxError()) {
8605                                if (act == ERROR_ACTION) this.lastErrorEndPosition = errorPos;
8606                                act = START_STATE;
8607                                this.stateStackTop = -1;
8608                                this.currentToken = getFirstToken();
8609                                if (DEBUG) System.out.println("!! Resume on syntax error"); //$NON-NLS-1$
8610                                continue ProcessTerminals;
8611                        }
8612                        act = ERROR_ACTION;
8613                        break ProcessTerminals;
8614                }
8615                if (act <= NUM_RULES) {
8616                        insertedSemicolon = false;
8617                        this.stateStackTop--;
8618 
8619                        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8620                                System.out.print("Reduce       - "); //$NON-NLS-1$
8621                        }
8622 
8623                } else if (act > ERROR_ACTION) { /* shift-reduce */
8624                        if (DEBUG) System.out.println("<<shift-reduce consume Token: "+scanner.toStringAction(this.currentToken)); //$NON-NLS-1$
8625                        consumeToken(this.currentToken);
8626                        if (this.currentElement != null) this.recoveryTokenCheck();
8627                        try {
8628                                prevPos = scanner.currentPosition;
8629                                prevToken = currentToken;
8630                                insertedSemicolon = false;
8631                                this.currentToken = this.scanner.getNextToken();
8632                                if (DEBUG) System.out.println(">>shift-reduce Next Token: "+scanner.dumpCurrent()); //$NON-NLS-1$
8633                        } catch(InvalidInputException e){
8634                                if (!this.hasReportedError){
8635                                        this.problemReporter().scannerError(this, e.getMessage());
8636                                        this.hasReportedError = true;
8637                                }
8638                                this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.currentPosition;
8639                                this.restartRecovery = true;
8640                        }
8641                        if(this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
8642                                this.jumpOverType();
8643                        }
8644                        act -= ERROR_ACTION;
8645 
8646                        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8647                                System.out.print("Shift/Reduce - (" + name[terminal_index[this.currentToken]]+") ");  //$NON-NLS-1$  //$NON-NLS-2$
8648                        }
8649 
8650                } else {
8651                    if (act < ACCEPT_ACTION) { /* shift */
8652                                if (DEBUG) System.out.println("<<shift consume Token: "+scanner.toStringAction(this.currentToken)); //$NON-NLS-1$
8653                                consumeToken(this.currentToken);
8654                                if (this.currentElement != null) this.recoveryTokenCheck();
8655                                try{
8656                                        prevPos = scanner.currentPosition;
8657                                        prevToken = currentToken;
8658                                        insertedSemicolon = false;
8659                                        this.currentToken = this.scanner.getNextToken();
8660                                        if (DEBUG) System.out.println(">>shift next Token: "+scanner.dumpCurrent()); //$NON-NLS-1$
8661                                } catch(InvalidInputException e){
8662                                        if (!this.hasReportedError){
8663                                                this.problemReporter().scannerError(this, e.getMessage());
8664                                                this.hasReportedError = true;
8665                                        }
8666                                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.currentPosition;
8667                                        this.restartRecovery = true;
8668                                }
8669                                if(this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
8670                                        this.jumpOverType();
8671                                }
8672                                if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8673                                        System.out.println("Shift        - (" + name[terminal_index[this.currentToken]]+")");  //$NON-NLS-1$  //$NON-NLS-2$
8674                                }
8675                                continue ProcessTerminals;
8676                        }
8677                        break ProcessTerminals;
8678                }
8679 
8680                // ProcessNonTerminals :
8681                do { /* reduce */
8682 
8683                        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8684                                System.out.println(name[non_terminal_index[lhs[act]]]);
8685                        }
8686 
8687                        consumeRule(act);
8688                        this.stateStackTop -= (rhs[act] - 1);
8689                        act = ntAction(this.stack[this.stateStackTop], lhs[act]);
8690                        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON && act <= NUM_RULES) {
8691                                System.out.print("             - ");  //$NON-NLS-1$
8692                                }
8693 
8694                } while (act <= NUM_RULES);
8695                if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8696                        System.out.println("----------------------------------------");  //$NON-NLS-1$
8697                }
8698        }
8699        if (DEBUG_AUTOMATON) {
8700                System.out.println("- End ----------------------------------");  //$NON-NLS-1$
8701        }
8702 
8703        endParse(act);
8704        // record all nls tags in the corresponding compilation unit
8705        final NLSTag[] tags = this.scanner.getNLSTags();
8706        if (tags != null) {
8707                this.compilationUnit.nlsTags = tags;
8708        }
8709 
8710        this.scanner.checkNonExternalizedStringLiterals = false;
8711        if (this.reportSyntaxErrorIsRequired && this.hasError && !(this.statementRecoveryActivated && DO_DIET_PARSE)) {
8712                if(!this.options.performStatementsRecovery) {
8713                        reportSyntaxErrors(isDietParse, oldFirstToken);
8714                } else {
8715                        RecoveryScannerData data = this.referenceContext.compilationResult().recoveryScannerData;
8716 
8717                        if(this.recoveryScanner == null) {
8718                                this.recoveryScanner = new RecoveryScanner(this.scanner, data);
8719                        } else {
8720                                this.recoveryScanner.setData(data);
8721                        }
8722 
8723                        this.recoveryScanner.setSource(scanner.source);
8724                        this.recoveryScanner.lineEnds = this.scanner.lineEnds;
8725                        this.recoveryScanner.linePtr = this.scanner.linePtr;
8726 
8727                        reportSyntaxErrors(isDietParse, oldFirstToken);
8728 
8729                        if(data == null) {
8730                                this.referenceContext.compilationResult().recoveryScannerData =
8731                                        this.recoveryScanner.getData();
8732                        }
8733 
8734                        if (this.methodRecoveryActivated && this.options.performStatementsRecovery && !this.enteredRecoverStatements) {
8735                                this.methodRecoveryActivated = false;
8736                                this.enteredRecoverStatements=true;
8737                                this.recoverStatements();
8738                                this.methodRecoveryActivated = true;
8739 
8740                                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
8741                        }
8742                }
8743        }
8744 
8745        if (DEBUG) System.out.println("-- EXIT FROM PARSE METHOD --");  //$NON-NLS-1$
8746}

8750public void parse(ConstructorDeclaration cd, CompilationUnitDeclaration unit, boolean recordLineSeparator) {
8751        //only parse the method body of cd
8752        //fill out its statements
8753 
8754        //convert bugs into parse error
8755 
8756        boolean oldMethodRecoveryActivated = this.methodRecoveryActivated;
8757        if(this.options.performMethodsFullRecovery) {
8758                this.methodRecoveryActivated = true;
8759        }
8760 
8761        initialize();
8762        goForBlockStatementsopt();
8763        if (recordLineSeparator) {
8764                this.scanner.recordLineSeparator = true;
8765        }
8766        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]++;
8767        pushOnRealBlockStack(0);
8768 
8769        this.referenceContext = cd;
8770        this.compilationUnit = unit;
8771 
8772        this.scanner.resetTo(cd.bodyStart, cd.bodyEnd);
8773        try {
8774                parse();
8775        } catch (AbortCompilation ex) {
8776                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
8777        } finally {
8778                this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]--;
8779                if(this.options.performStatementsRecovery) {
8780                        this.methodRecoveryActivated = oldMethodRecoveryActivated;
8781                }
8782        }
8783 
8784        checkNonNLSAfterBodyEnd(cd.declarationSourceEnd);
8785 
8786        if (this.lastAct == ERROR_ACTION) {
8787                initialize();
8788                return;
8789        }
8790 
8791        //statements
8792        cd.explicitDeclarations = this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr--];
8793        int length;
8794        if (astLengthPtr > -1 && (length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
8795                this.astPtr -= length;
8796                if (this.astStack[this.astPtr + 1] instanceof ExplicitConstructorCall)
8797                        //avoid a isSomeThing that would only be used here BUT what is faster between two alternatives ?
8798                        {
8799                        System.arraycopy(
8800                                this.astStack,
8801                                this.astPtr + 2,
8802                                cd.statements = new Statement[length - 1],
8803                                0,
8804                                length - 1);
8805                        cd.constructorCall = (ExplicitConstructorCall) this.astStack[this.astPtr + 1];
8806                } else { //need to add explicitly the super();
8807                        System.arraycopy(
8808                                this.astStack,
8809                                this.astPtr + 1,
8810                                cd.statements = new Statement[length],
8811                                0,
8812                                length);
8813                        cd.constructorCall = SuperReference.implicitSuperConstructorCall();
8814                }
8815        } else {
8816                cd.constructorCall = SuperReference.implicitSuperConstructorCall();
8817                if (!containsComment(cd.bodyStart, cd.bodyEnd)) {
8818                        cd.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
8819                }
8820        }
8821

8823                cd.constructorCall.sourceEnd = cd.sourceEnd;
8824                cd.constructorCall.sourceStart = cd.sourceStart;
8825        }

8877public CompilationUnitDeclaration parse(
8878        ICompilationUnit sourceUnit,
8879        CompilationResult compilationResult,
8880        int start,
8881        int end) {
8882        // parses a compilation unit and manages error handling (even bugs....)
8883 
8884        CompilationUnitDeclaration unit;
8885        try {
8886                /* automaton initialization */
8887                initialize(true);
8888                goForCompilationUnit();
8889 
8890                /* unit creation */
8891                this.referenceContext =
8892                        this.compilationUnit =
8893                                new CompilationUnitDeclaration(
8894                                        this.problemReporter,
8895                                        compilationResult,
8896                                        0);
8897 
8898 
8899                initializeInferenceEngine(this.compilationUnit);
8900 
8901                /* scanners initialization */
8902                char[] contents;
8903                try {
8904                        contents = sourceUnit.getContents();
8905                } catch(AbortCompilationUnit abortException) {
8906                        this.problemReporter().cannotReadSource(this.compilationUnit, abortException, this.options.verbose);
8907                        contents = CharOperation.NO_CHAR; // pretend empty from thereon
8908                }
8909                this.scanner.setSource(contents);
8910                this.compilationUnit.sourceEnd = this.scanner.source.length - 1;
8911                if (end != -1) this.scanner.resetTo(start, end);
8912                if (this.javadocParser != null && this.javadocParser.checkDocComment) {
8913                        this.javadocParser.scanner.setSource(contents);
8914                        if (end != -1) {
8915                                this.javadocParser.scanner.resetTo(start, end);
8916                        }
8917                }
8918                /* run automaton */
8919if (false)
8920        System.out.println("parsing "+new String(sourceUnit.getFileName())); //$NON-NLS-1$
8921                parse();
8922        } finally {
8923                unit = this.compilationUnit;
8924                this.compilationUnit = null; // reset parser
8925                // tag unit has having read bodies
8926                if (!this.diet) unit.bits |= ASTNode.HasAllMethodBodies;
8927        }
8928        return unit;
8929}

8931public void initializeInferenceEngine(CompilationUnitDeclaration compilationUnitDeclaration) {
8932        if (this.inferenceEngines==null)
8933                this.inferenceEngines =  InferrenceManager.getInstance().getInferenceEngines(compilationUnitDeclaration);
8934        for (int i = 0; i <  this.inferenceEngines.length; i++) {
8935                this.inferenceEngines[i].initializeOptions(this.options.inferOptions);
8936        }
