8939public void parse(
8940        Initializer initializer,
8941        TypeDeclaration type,
8942        CompilationUnitDeclaration unit) {
8943        //only parse the method body of md
8944        //fill out method statements
8945 
8946        //convert bugs into parse error
8947 
8948        boolean oldMethodRecoveryActivated = this.methodRecoveryActivated;
8949        if(this.options.performMethodsFullRecovery) {
8950                this.methodRecoveryActivated = true;
8951        }
8952 
8953        initialize();
8954        goForBlockStatementsopt();
8955        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]++;
8956        pushOnRealBlockStack(0);
8957 
8958        this.referenceContext = type;
8959        this.compilationUnit = unit;
8960 
8961        this.scanner.resetTo(initializer.bodyStart, initializer.bodyEnd); // just on the beginning {
8962        try {
8963                parse();
8964        } catch (AbortCompilation ex) {
8965                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
8966        } finally {
8967                this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]--;
8968                if(this.options.performStatementsRecovery) {
8969                        this.methodRecoveryActivated = oldMethodRecoveryActivated;
8970                }
8971        }
8972 
8973        checkNonNLSAfterBodyEnd(initializer.declarationSourceEnd);
8974 
8975        if (this.lastAct == ERROR_ACTION) {
8976                return;
8977        }
8978 
8979        //refill statements
8980        initializer.block.explicitDeclarations = this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr--];
8981        int length;
8982        if (astLengthPtr > -1 && (length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) > 0) {
8983                System.arraycopy(this.astStack, (this.astPtr -= length) + 1, initializer.block.statements = new Statement[length], 0, length);
8984        } else {
8985                // check whether this block at least contains some comment in it
8986                if (!containsComment(initializer.block.sourceStart, initializer.block.sourceEnd)) {
8987                        initializer.block.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
8988                }
8989        }
8990 
8991        // mark initializer with local type if one was found during parsing
8992        if ((type.bits & ASTNode.HasLocalType) != 0) {
8993                initializer.bits |= ASTNode.HasLocalType;
8994        }
8995}
8996// A P I
8997public void parse(MethodDeclaration md, CompilationUnitDeclaration unit) {
8998        //only parse the method body of md
8999        //fill out method statements
9000 
9001        //convert bugs into parse error
9002 
9003        if (md.isAbstract())
9004                return;
9005        if (md.isNative())
9006                return;
9007        if ((md.modifiers & ExtraCompilerModifiers.AccSemicolonBody) != 0)
9008                return;
9009 
9010        boolean oldMethodRecoveryActivated = this.methodRecoveryActivated;
9011        if(this.options.performMethodsFullRecovery) {
9012                this.methodRecoveryActivated = true;
9013                this.rParenPos = md.sourceEnd;
9014        }
9015        initialize();
9016        goForBlockStatementsopt();
9017        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]++;
9018        pushOnRealBlockStack(0);
9019 
9020        this.referenceContext = md;
9021        this.compilationUnit = unit;
9022 
9023        this.scanner.resetTo(md.bodyStart, md.bodyEnd);
9024        // reset the scanner to parser from { down to }
9025        try {
9026                parse();
9027        } catch (AbortCompilation ex) {
9028                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
9029        } finally {
9030                this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]--;
9031                if(this.options.performStatementsRecovery) {
9032                        this.methodRecoveryActivated = oldMethodRecoveryActivated;
9033                }
9034        }
9035 
9036        checkNonNLSAfterBodyEnd(md.declarationSourceEnd);
9037 
9038        if (this.lastAct == ERROR_ACTION) {
9039                return;
9040        }
9041 
9042        //refill statements
9043        md.explicitDeclarations = this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr--];
9044        int length;
9045        if (astLengthPtr > -1 && (length = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
9046                System.arraycopy(
9047                        this.astStack,
9048                        (this.astPtr -= length) + 1,
9049                        md.statements = new Statement[length],
9050                        0,
9051                        length);
9052        } else {
9053                if (!containsComment(md.bodyStart, md.bodyEnd)) {
9054                        md.bits |= ASTNode.UndocumentedEmptyBlock;
9055                }
9056        }
9057}
9058public ASTNode[] parseClassBodyDeclarations(char[] source, int offset, int length, CompilationUnitDeclaration unit) {
9059        /* automaton initialization */
9060        initialize();
9061        goForClassBodyDeclarations();
9062        /* scanner initialization */
9063        this.scanner.setSource(source);
9064        this.scanner.resetTo(offset, offset + length - 1);
9065        if (this.javadocParser != null && this.javadocParser.checkDocComment) {
9066                this.javadocParser.scanner.setSource(source);
9067                this.javadocParser.scanner.resetTo(offset, offset + length - 1);
9068        }
9069 
9070        /* type declaration should be parsed as member type declaration */
9071        this.nestedType = 1;
9072 
9073        /* unit creation */
9074        this.referenceContext = unit;
9075        this.compilationUnit = unit;
9076 
9077        /* run automaton */
9078        try {
9079                parse();
9080        } catch (AbortCompilation ex) {
9081                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
9082        }
9083 
9084        if (this.lastAct == ERROR_ACTION || this.hasError) {
9085                return null;
9086        }
9087        int astLength;
9088        if (astLengthPtr > -1 && (astLength = this.astLengthStack[this.astLengthPtr--]) != 0) {
9089                ASTNode[] result = new ASTNode[astLength];
9090                this.astPtr -= astLength;
9091                System.arraycopy(this.astStack, this.astPtr + 1, result, 0, astLength);
9092                return result;
9093        }
9094        return null;
9095}
9096public Expression parseExpression(char[] source, int offset, int length, CompilationUnitDeclaration unit) {
9097

9099        goForExpression();
9100        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]++;
9101 
9102        this.referenceContext = unit;
9103        this.compilationUnit = unit;
9104 
9105        this.scanner.setSource(source);
9106        this.scanner.resetTo(offset, offset + length - 1);
9107        try {
9108                parse();
9109        } catch (AbortCompilation ex) {
9110                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
9111        } finally {
9112                this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]--;
9113        }
9114 
9115        if (this.lastAct == ERROR_ACTION) {
9116                return null;
9117        }
9118 
9119        return this.expressionStack[this.expressionPtr];

9146public void parseStatements(ReferenceContext rc, int start, int end, TypeDeclaration[] types, CompilationUnitDeclaration unit) {
9147        boolean oldStatementRecoveryEnabled = this.statementRecoveryActivated;
9148        this.statementRecoveryActivated = true;
9149 
9150        initialize();
9151 
9152        if (rc instanceof CompilationUnitDeclaration)
9153                goForCompilationUnit();
9154        else
9155                goForBlockStatementsopt();
9156        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]++;
9157        pushOnRealBlockStack(0);
9158 
9159        pushOnAstLengthStack(0);
9160 
9161        this.referenceContext = rc;
9162        this.compilationUnit = unit;
9163 
9164        this.pendingRecoveredType = null;
9165 
9166        if(types != null && types.length > 0) {
9167                this.recoveredTypes = types;
9168                this.recoveredTypePtr = 0;
9169                this.nextTypeStart =
9170                        this.recoveredTypes[0].allocation == null
9171                                ? this.recoveredTypes[0].declarationSourceStart
9172                                                : this.recoveredTypes[0].allocation.sourceStart;
9173        } else {
9174                this.recoveredTypes = null;
9175                this.recoveredTypePtr = -1;
9176                this.nextTypeStart = -1;
9177        }
9178 
9179        this.scanner.resetTo(start, end);
9180        // reset the scanner to parser from { down to }
9181 
9182        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.initialPosition;
9183 
9184 
9185        this.stateStackTop = -1;
9186 
9187        try {
9188                parse();
9189        } catch (AbortCompilation ex) {
9190                this.lastAct = ERROR_ACTION;
9191        } finally {
9192                this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType]--;
9193                this.recoveredTypes = null;
9194                this.statementRecoveryActivated = oldStatementRecoveryEnabled;
9195        }
9196 
9197        checkNonNLSAfterBodyEnd(end);
9198}
9199public void persistLineSeparatorPositions() {
9200        if (this.scanner.recordLineSeparator) {
9201                this.compilationUnit.compilationResult.lineSeparatorPositions = this.scanner.getLineEnds();
9202        }
9203}
9204/*
9205 * Prepares the state of the parser to go for BlockStatements.
9206 */
9207protected void prepareForBlockStatements() {
9208        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType = 0] = 1;
9209        this.variablesCounter[this.nestedType] = 0;
9210        this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr = 1] = 0;
9211}
9212/**
9213 * Returns this parser's problem reporter initialized with its reference context.
9214 * Also it is assumed that a problem is going to be reported, so initializes
9215 * the compilation result's line positions.
9216 *
9217 * @return ProblemReporter
9218 */
9219public ProblemReporter problemReporter(){
9220        if (this.scanner.recordLineSeparator) {
9221                if (this.compilationUnit!=null)
9222                        this.compilationUnit.compilationResult.lineSeparatorPositions = this.scanner.getLineEnds();
9223        }
9224        this.problemReporter.referenceContext = this.referenceContext;
9225        return this.problemReporter;
9226}
9227protected void pushIdentifier() {
9228        /*push the consumeToken on the identifier stack.
9229        Increase the total number of identifier in the stack.
9230        identifierPtr points on the next top */
9231 
9232        int stackLength = this.identifierStack.length;
9233        if (++this.identifierPtr >= stackLength) {
9234                System.arraycopy(
9235                        this.identifierStack, 0,
9236                        this.identifierStack = new char[stackLength + 20][], 0,
9237                        stackLength);
9238                System.arraycopy(
9239                        this.identifierPositionStack, 0,
9240                        this.identifierPositionStack = new long[stackLength + 20], 0,
9241                        stackLength);
9242        }
9243        this.identifierStack[this.identifierPtr] = this.scanner.getCurrentIdentifierSource();
9244        this.identifierPositionStack[this.identifierPtr] =
9245                (((long) this.scanner.startPosition) << 32) + (this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
9246 
9247        stackLength = this.identifierLengthStack.length;
9248        if (++this.identifierLengthPtr >= stackLength) {
9249                System.arraycopy(
9250                        this.identifierLengthStack, 0,
9251                        this.identifierLengthStack = new int[stackLength + 10], 0,
9252                        stackLength);
9253        }
9254        this.identifierLengthStack[this.identifierLengthPtr] = 1;
9255}

9400protected void recoverStatements() {
9401        class MethodVisitor extends ASTVisitor {
9402                public ASTVisitor typeVisitor;
9403 
9404                TypeDeclaration enclosingType; // used only for initializer
9405 
9406                TypeDeclaration[] types = new TypeDeclaration[0];
9407                int typePtr = -1;
9408                public boolean visit(ConstructorDeclaration constructorDeclaration, ClassScope scope) {
9409                        typePtr = -1;
9410                        return true;
9411                }
9412                public boolean visit(Initializer initializer, MethodScope scope) {
9413                        typePtr = -1;
9414                        return true;
9415                }
9416                public boolean visit(MethodDeclaration methodDeclaration,Scope scope) {
9417                        typePtr = -1;
9418                        return true;
9419                }
9420                public boolean visit(TypeDeclaration typeDeclaration, BlockScope scope) {
9421                        return this.visit(typeDeclaration);
9422                }
9423                public boolean visit(TypeDeclaration typeDeclaration, Scope scope) {
9424                        return this.visit(typeDeclaration);
9425                }
9426                private boolean visit(TypeDeclaration typeDeclaration) {
9427                        if(this.types.length <= ++this.typePtr) {
9428                                int length = this.typePtr;
9429                                System.arraycopy(this.types, 0, this.types = new TypeDeclaration[length * 2 + 1], 0, length);
9430                        }
9431                        this.types[this.typePtr] = typeDeclaration;
9432                        return false;
9433                }
9434                public void endVisit(ConstructorDeclaration constructorDeclaration, ClassScope scope) {
9435                        this.endVisitMethod(constructorDeclaration, scope);
9436                }
9437                public void endVisit(MethodDeclaration methodDeclaration, Scope scope) {
9438                        this.endVisitMethod(methodDeclaration, scope);
9439                }
9440                private void endVisitMethod(AbstractMethodDeclaration methodDeclaration, Scope scope) {
9441                        TypeDeclaration[] foundTypes = null;
9442//                        int length = 0;
9443//                        if(this.typePtr > -1) {
9444//                                length = this.typePtr + 1;
9445//                                foundTypes = new TypeDeclaration[length];
9446//                                System.arraycopy(this.types, 0, foundTypes, 0, length);
9447//                        }
9448                        ReferenceContext oldContext = Parser.this.referenceContext;
9449                        Parser.this.recoveryScanner.resetTo(methodDeclaration.bodyStart, methodDeclaration.bodyEnd);
9450                        Scanner oldScanner = Parser.this.scanner;
9451                        Parser.this.scanner = Parser.this.recoveryScanner;
9452                        Parser.this.parseStatements(
9453                                        methodDeclaration,
9454                                        methodDeclaration.bodyStart,
9455                                        methodDeclaration.bodyEnd,
9456                                        foundTypes,
9457                                        compilationUnit);
9458                        Parser.this.scanner = oldScanner;
9459                        Parser.this.referenceContext = oldContext;
9460 
9461//                        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
9462//                                foundTypes[i].traverse(typeVisitor, scope);
9463//                        }
9464                }
9465                public void endVisit(Initializer initializer, MethodScope scope) {
9466                        TypeDeclaration[] foundTypes = null;
9467                        int length = 0;
9468                        if(this.typePtr > -1) {
9469                                length = this.typePtr + 1;
9470                                foundTypes = new TypeDeclaration[length];
9471                                System.arraycopy(this.types, 0, foundTypes, 0, length);
9472                        }
9473                        ReferenceContext oldContext = Parser.this.referenceContext;
9474                        Parser.this.recoveryScanner.resetTo(initializer.bodyStart, initializer.bodyEnd);
9475                        Scanner oldScanner = Parser.this.scanner;
9476                        Parser.this.scanner = Parser.this.recoveryScanner;
9477                        Parser.this.parseStatements(
9478                                        this.enclosingType,
9479                                        initializer.bodyStart,
9480                                        initializer.bodyEnd,
9481                                        foundTypes,
9482                                        compilationUnit);
9483                        Parser.this.scanner = oldScanner;
9484                        Parser.this.referenceContext = oldContext;
9485 
9486                        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
9487                                foundTypes[i].traverse(typeVisitor, scope);
9488                        }
9489                }

9512                private boolean visit(TypeDeclaration typeDeclaration) {
9513                        if(this.types.length <= ++this.typePtr) {
9514                                int length = this.typePtr;
9515                                System.arraycopy(this.types, 0, this.types = new TypeDeclaration[length * 2 + 1], 0, length);
9516                        }
9517                        this.types[this.typePtr] = typeDeclaration;
9518                        return true;
9519                }
9520                public boolean visit(ConstructorDeclaration constructorDeclaration, ClassScope scope) {
9521                        if(constructorDeclaration.isDefaultConstructor()) return false;
9522 
9523                        constructorDeclaration.traverse(methodVisitor, scope);
9524                        return false;
9525                }

9527                        methodVisitor.enclosingType = this.types[typePtr];

9529                        return false;
9530                }
9531                public boolean visit(MethodDeclaration methodDeclaration, Scope scope) {
9532                        methodDeclaration.traverse(methodVisitor, scope);
9533                        return false;
9534                }
9535        }
9536 
9537        if (false)
9538        {
9539        MethodVisitor methodVisitor = new MethodVisitor();
9540        TypeVisitor typeVisitor = new TypeVisitor();

9542        typeVisitor.methodVisitor = methodVisitor;
9543 
9544        if(this.referenceContext instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration) {
9545                ((AbstractMethodDeclaration)this.referenceContext).traverse(methodVisitor, (Scope)null);
9546        }else if(this.referenceContext instanceof CompilationUnitDeclaration) {
9547                CompilationUnitDeclaration compilationUnitDeclaration=(CompilationUnitDeclaration)this.referenceContext;
9548                if (compilationUnitDeclaration.statements!=null)
9549                        for (int i = 0; i < compilationUnitDeclaration.statements.length; i++) {
9550                                if( compilationUnitDeclaration.statements[i] instanceof AbstractMethodDeclaration)
9551                                        ((AbstractMethodDeclaration)compilationUnitDeclaration.statements[i] ).traverse(methodVisitor, (Scope)null);
9552                        }
9553        } else if(this.referenceContext instanceof TypeDeclaration) {
9554                TypeDeclaration typeContext = (TypeDeclaration)this.referenceContext;
9555 
9556                int length = typeContext.fields.length;
9557                for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
9558                        final FieldDeclaration fieldDeclaration = typeContext.fields[i];
9559                        switch(fieldDeclaration.getKind()) {
9560                                case AbstractVariableDeclaration.INITIALIZER:
9561                                        methodVisitor.enclosingType = typeContext;
9562                                        ((Initializer) fieldDeclaration).traverse(methodVisitor, (MethodScope)null);
9563                                        break;
9564                        }
9565                }
9566        }
9567        }
9568        else
9569        {
9570                CompilationUnitDeclaration compilationUnitDeclaration=(CompilationUnitDeclaration)this.referenceContext;
9571 
9572                ReferenceContext oldContext = Parser.this.referenceContext;
9573                int start = compilationUnitDeclaration.sourceStart;
9574                int end = compilationUnitDeclaration.sourceEnd;
9575                Parser.this.recoveryScanner.resetTo(start, end);
9576                Scanner oldScanner = Parser.this.scanner;
9577                Parser.this.scanner = Parser.this.recoveryScanner;
9578                /* unit creation */
9579                this.referenceContext =
9580                        this.compilationUnit = compilationUnitDeclaration=
9581                                new CompilationUnitDeclaration(
9582                                        this.problemReporter,
9583                                        compilationUnitDeclaration.compilationResult,
9584                                        end);
9585 
9586                Parser.this.parseStatements(
9587                                compilationUnitDeclaration,
9588                                start,
9589                                end,
9590                                null,
9591                                compilationUnit);
9592                Parser.this.scanner = oldScanner;
9593                Parser.this.referenceContext = oldContext;
9594        }

9599public void recoveryExitFromVariable() {
9600        if(this.currentElement != null && this.currentElement.parent != null) {
9601                if(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredLocalVariable) {
9602 
9603                        int end = ((RecoveredLocalVariable)this.currentElement).localDeclaration.sourceEnd;
9604                        this.currentElement.updateSourceEndIfNecessary(end);
9605                        this.currentElement = this.currentElement.parent;
9606                } else if(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredField
9607                        && !(this.currentElement instanceof RecoveredInitializer)) {
9608 
9609                        int end = ((RecoveredField)this.currentElement).fieldDeclaration.sourceEnd;
9610                        this.currentElement.updateSourceEndIfNecessary(end);
9611                        this.currentElement = this.currentElement.parent;
9612                }
9613        }

9615/* Token check performed on every token shift once having entered
9616 * recovery mode.
9617 */
9618public void recoveryTokenCheck() {
9619        switch (this.currentToken) {
9620                case TokenNameLBRACE :
9621                        RecoveredElement newElement = null;
9622                        if(!this.ignoreNextOpeningBrace) {
9623                                newElement = this.currentElement.updateOnOpeningBrace(this.scanner.startPosition - 1, this.scanner.currentPosition - 1);
9624                        }
9625                        this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.currentPosition;
9626                        if (newElement != null){ // null means nothing happened
9627                                this.restartRecovery = true; // opening brace detected
9628                                this.currentElement = newElement;
9629                        }
9630                        break;
9631 
9632                case TokenNameRBRACE :
9633                        this.rBraceStart = this.scanner.startPosition - 1;
9634                        this.rBraceEnd = this.scanner.currentPosition - 1;
9635                        this.endPosition = this.flushCommentsDefinedPriorTo(this.rBraceEnd);
9636                        newElement =
9637                                this.currentElement.updateOnClosingBrace(this.scanner.startPosition, this.rBraceEnd);
9638                                this.lastCheckPoint = this.scanner.currentPosition;
9639                        if (newElement != this.currentElement){
9640                                this.currentElement = newElement;
9641//                                if (newElement instanceof RecoveredField && this.dietInt <= 0) {
9642//                                        if (((RecoveredField)newElement).fieldDeclaration.type == null) { // enum constant
9643//                                                this.isInsideEnumConstantPart = true; // restore status
9644//                                        }
9645//                                }
9646                        }
9647                        break;
9648                case TokenNameSEMICOLON :
9649                        this.endStatementPosition = this.scanner.currentPosition - 1;
9650                        this.endPosition = this.scanner.startPosition - 1;
9651                        this.lastCheckPoint=this.scanner.currentPosition;
9652//                        RecoveredType currentType = this.currentRecoveryType();
9653//                        if(currentType != null) {
9654//                                currentType.insideEnumConstantPart = false;
9655//                        }
9656                        // fall through
9657                default : {
9658                        if (this.rBraceEnd > this.rBraceSuccessorStart && this.scanner.currentPosition != this.scanner.startPosition){
9659                                this.rBraceSuccessorStart = this.scanner.startPosition;
9660                        }
9661                        break;
9662                }
9663        }
9664        this.ignoreNextOpeningBrace = false;
9665}
9666 
9667protected boolean shouldInsertSemicolon(int prevpos, int prevtoken) {
9668        if ( this.currentToken == TokenNameRBRACE ||
9669                 scanner.getLineNumber(scanner.currentPosition) > scanner.getLineNumber(prevpos)
9670                 || this.currentToken==TokenNameEOF
9671                )
9672                return true;
9673        return false;
9674}

9754/*
9755 * Reset context so as to resume to regular parse loop
9756 */
9757protected void resetStacks() {
9758 
9759        this.astPtr = -1;
9760        this.astLengthPtr = -1;
9761        this.expressionPtr = -1;
9762        this.expressionLengthPtr = -1;
9763        this.identifierPtr = -1;
9764        this.identifierLengthPtr        = -1;
9765        this.intPtr = -1;
9766        this.nestedMethod[this.nestedType = 0] = 0; // need to reset for further reuse
9767        this.variablesCounter[this.nestedType] = 0;
9768        this.dimensions = 0 ;
9769        this.realBlockStack[this.realBlockPtr = 0] = 0;
9770        this.recoveredStaticInitializerStart = 0;
9771        this.listLength = 0;
9772        this.listTypeParameterLength = 0;
9773 
9774        this.genericsIdentifiersLengthPtr = -1;
9775        this.genericsLengthPtr = -1;
9776        this.genericsPtr = -1;
9777}
9778/*
9779 * Reset context so as to resume to regular parse loop
9780 * If unable to reset for resuming, answers false.
9781 *
9782 * Move checkpoint location, reset internal stacks and
9783 * decide which grammar goal is activated.
9784 */
9785protected boolean resumeAfterRecovery() {
9786        if(!this.methodRecoveryActivated && !this.statementRecoveryActivated) {
9787 
9788                // reset internal stacks
9789                this.resetStacks();
9790                this.resetModifiers();
9791 
9792                /* attempt to move checkpoint location */
9793                if (!this.moveRecoveryCheckpoint()) {
9794                        return false;
9795                }
9796 
9797                // only look for headers
9798                if (this.referenceContext instanceof CompilationUnitDeclaration){
9799                        if (DO_DIET_PARSE)
9800                        {
9801                                goForHeaders();
9802                                this.diet = true; // passed this point, will not consider method bodies
9803                        }
9804                        else
9805                                goForProgramElements();
9806                        return true;
9807                }
9808 
9809                // does not know how to restart
9810                return false;
9811        } else if(!this.statementRecoveryActivated || !DO_DIET_PARSE) {
9812 
9813                // reset internal stacks
9814                this.resetStacks();
9815                this.resetModifiers();
9816 
9817                /* attempt to move checkpoint location */
9818                if (!this.moveRecoveryCheckpoint()) {
9819                        return false;
9820                }
9821 
9822                // only look for headers
9823                if (DO_DIET_PARSE)
9824                        goForHeaders();
9825                else
9826                        goForProgramElements();
9827                return true;
9828        } else {
9829                return false;
9830        }
9831}
9832protected boolean resumeOnSyntaxError() {
9833        this.checkExternalizeStrings = false;
9834        this.scanner.checkNonExternalizedStringLiterals = false;
9835        /* request recovery initialization */
9836        if (this.currentElement == null){
9837                // Reset javadoc before restart parsing after recovery
9838                this.javadoc = null;
9839 
9840                // do not investigate deeper in statement recovery
9841                if (this.statementRecoveryActivated) return false;
9842 
9843                // build some recovered elements
9844                this.currentElement = buildInitialRecoveryState();
9845        }
9846        /* do not investigate deeper in recovery when no recovered element */
9847        if (this.currentElement == null) return false;
9848 
9849        /* manual forced recovery restart - after headers */
9850        if (this.restartRecovery){
9851                this.restartRecovery = false;
9852        }
9853        /* update recovery state with current error state of the parser */
9854        this.updateRecoveryState();
9855 
9856        /* attempt to reset state in order to resume to parse loop */
9857        return this.resumeAfterRecovery();
9858}
9859public void setMethodsFullRecovery(boolean enabled) {
9860        this.options.performMethodsFullRecovery = enabled;
9861}
9862public void setStatementsRecovery(boolean enabled) {
9863        if(enabled) this.options.performMethodsFullRecovery = true;
9864        this.options.performStatementsRecovery = enabled;
9865}

9908 
9909        s = s + "genericsLengthStack : int["+(this.genericsLengthPtr + 1)+"] = {"; //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$
9910        for (int i = 0; i <= this.genericsLengthPtr; i++) {
9911                s = s + this.genericsLengthStack[i] + ","; //$NON-NLS-1$
9912        }
9913        s = s + "}\n"; //$NON-NLS-1$
9914 
9915        s = s + "genericsPtr : int = " + String.valueOf(this.genericsPtr) + "\n"; //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$
9916 
9917        s = s + "\n\n\n----------------Scanner--------------\n" + this.scanner.toString(); //$NON-NLS-1$
9918        return s;
9919 
9920}
9921/*
9922 * Update recovery state based on current parser/scanner state
9923 */
9924protected void updateRecoveryState() {
9925 
9926        /* expose parser state to recovery state */
9927        this.currentElement.updateFromParserState();
9928 
9929        /* check and update recovered state based on current token,
9930                this action is also performed when shifting token after recovery
9931                got activated once.
9932        */
9933        this.recoveryTokenCheck();
9934}
9935protected void updateSourceDeclarationParts(int variableDeclaratorsCounter) {
9936        //fields is a definition of fields that are grouped together like in
9937        //public int[] a, b[], c
9938        //which results into 3 fields.
9939 
9940        FieldDeclaration field;
9941        int endTypeDeclarationPosition =
9942                -1 + this.astStack[this.astPtr - variableDeclaratorsCounter + 1].sourceStart;
9943        for (int i = 0; i < variableDeclaratorsCounter - 1; i++) {
9944                //last one is special(see below)
9945                field = (FieldDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr - i - 1];
9946                field.endPart1Position = endTypeDeclarationPosition;
9947                field.endPart2Position = -1 + this.astStack[this.astPtr - i].sourceStart;
9948        }
9949        //last one
9950        (field = (FieldDeclaration) this.astStack[this.astPtr]).endPart1Position =
9951                endTypeDeclarationPosition;
9952        field.endPart2Position = field.declarationSourceEnd;
9953 
9954}
9955protected void updateSourcePosition(Expression exp) {
9956        //update the source Position of the expression
9957 
9958        //this.intStack : int int
9959        //-->
9960        //this.intStack :
9961 
9962        exp.sourceEnd = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
9963        exp.sourceStart = this.intStack[this.intPtr--];
9964}
9965 
9966public void inferTypes(CompilationUnitDeclaration parsedUnit, CompilerOptions compileOptions) {
9967        if (parsedUnit.typesHaveBeenInferred)
9968                return;
9969        if (compileOptions==null)
9970                compileOptions=this.options;
9971        
9972        if (this.inferenceEngines==null)
9973                initializeInferenceEngine(parsedUnit);
9974//        InferEngine inferEngine=compileOptions.inferOptions.createEngine();
9975        for (int i=0;i<this.inferenceEngines.length;i++)
9976        {
9977                        InferEngine engine=this.inferenceEngines[i];
9978                        engine.initialize();
9979                        engine.setCompilationUnit(parsedUnit);
9980                        engine.doInfer();
9981 
9982        }
9983        parsedUnit.typesHaveBeenInferred=true;
9984}
